1
00:03:15,778 --> 00:03:18,780
â™ª It's a mad, mad, mad...

2
00:05:12,228 --> 00:05:13,353
Whoa!

3
00:05:13,521 --> 00:05:16,189
Did you see it,
the way he went sailing right out there?

4
00:05:17,400 --> 00:05:20,360
- He just went sailing out there.
- It was just terrible.

5
00:05:20,528 --> 00:05:22,154
He must have been doing over 80.

6
00:05:22,322 --> 00:05:25,407
An ambulance...
We ought to call an ambulance.

7
00:05:26,492 --> 00:05:27,951
Look at that car.

8
00:05:28,536 --> 00:05:31,163
He must have gone by you
doing 90 miles an hour.

9
00:05:31,331 --> 00:05:34,791
He was passing me! I never saw
such a crazy thing in my life!

10
00:05:34,959 --> 00:05:36,960
- Let's get down there.
- Let's go.

11
00:05:37,587 --> 00:05:39,087
We're going down there.

12
00:05:39,255 --> 00:05:41,298
Russell, be careful.
Remember your condition.

13
00:05:41,466 --> 00:05:43,091
Eh!

14
00:05:43,259 --> 00:05:46,261
Boy, the way he just
sailed out there...

15
00:05:47,680 --> 00:05:49,598
Look out.

16
00:05:52,310 --> 00:05:54,102
There's nobody in the car.

17
00:05:54,729 --> 00:05:56,646
- He's right.
- What do you mean, nobody?

18
00:05:56,814 --> 00:05:57,731
There he is.

19
00:05:57,899 --> 00:05:59,733
Holy smoke!

20
00:06:05,448 --> 00:06:07,949
How about that?
This guy's still alive.

21
00:06:08,117 --> 00:06:09,493
He's still alive.

22
00:06:09,702 --> 00:06:11,328
We ought to call an ambulance.

23
00:06:11,496 --> 00:06:14,748
I don't know how he survived, the way
you went sailing right out there.

24
00:06:14,916 --> 00:06:18,043
I'm not a doctor,
but I have some medical experience.

25
00:06:18,211 --> 00:06:19,127
I'm a dentist.

26
00:06:19,295 --> 00:06:21,963
Do you think you're hurt real bad?

27
00:06:24,300 --> 00:06:25,759
Is he kidding?

28
00:06:25,927 --> 00:06:28,178
Hold on, we're gonna get you
to a hospital.

29
00:06:28,346 --> 00:06:32,474
You move me,
I'll break up in little pieces.

30
00:06:32,642 --> 00:06:33,975
But what a deal.

31
00:06:34,143 --> 00:06:36,686
Look, there's this dough, see?

32
00:06:36,854 --> 00:06:40,649
There's all this dough: $350,000!

33
00:06:40,817 --> 00:06:43,026
Do you hear what I'm saying?

34
00:06:43,194 --> 00:06:46,488
$350,000!

35
00:06:46,656 --> 00:06:51,159
In the park, in Rosita,
Rosita Beach State Park...

36
00:06:51,327 --> 00:06:54,162
...just south of Dago in Santa Rosita.

37
00:06:54,330 --> 00:06:57,416
It's in this box buried under this...

38
00:07:01,295 --> 00:07:03,213
Buried under this big W.

39
00:07:03,381 --> 00:07:04,756
You'll see it.

40
00:07:04,924 --> 00:07:08,677
You'll see it under this...
under this big W.

41
00:07:08,845 --> 00:07:13,098
You can't miss it, a big... a big W.

42
00:07:13,266 --> 00:07:17,310
And it's been there...
And it's been laying there for 15 years.

43
00:07:18,813 --> 00:07:20,772
He's very sick. He may die.

44
00:07:20,940 --> 00:07:23,692
Listen. I tell you,
I'm giving it to you.

45
00:07:23,860 --> 00:07:26,611
And don't let them kid you.
Don't let them kid you.

46
00:07:26,779 --> 00:07:31,533
Don't let them give you the business
because it was mine and I paid for it...

47
00:07:31,701 --> 00:07:34,953
...paid for every lousy buck of it.

48
00:07:35,121 --> 00:07:36,413
But watch out.

49
00:07:36,581 --> 00:07:38,039
Watch out for the bulls.

50
00:07:38,708 --> 00:07:42,294
Lousy, stinking bulls are everywhere.

51
00:07:42,462 --> 00:07:44,588
Bulls all over the place.

52
00:07:44,755 --> 00:07:46,840
You just drive down and dig it up.

53
00:07:47,008 --> 00:07:49,301
Dig it all up.

54
00:07:52,054 --> 00:07:53,388
And then...

55
00:07:53,556 --> 00:07:55,807
And then you fix yourselves all up.

56
00:07:55,975 --> 00:07:57,392
Fix yourselves all up.

57
00:07:57,560 --> 00:08:01,396
Walk down the street like a king,
back to the old neighborhood.

58
00:08:01,564 --> 00:08:04,316
See the fellas, the dames...

59
00:08:04,484 --> 00:08:07,611
...the dames, all with a big hello...

60
00:08:08,446 --> 00:08:11,239
...a big hello for old Smiler.

61
00:08:11,407 --> 00:08:13,408
Good old Smiler...

62
00:08:14,911 --> 00:08:17,871
...everybody's friend.

63
00:08:19,499 --> 00:08:21,583
Everybody's...

64
00:08:26,589 --> 00:08:30,592
- Aunt Belle, I didn't mean to do it!
- Holy mackerel! Take it easy.

65
00:08:30,760 --> 00:08:34,679
Please, say it don't make
any difference, Aunt Belle!

66
00:08:34,847 --> 00:08:37,307
Please, you got to say...

67
00:08:37,475 --> 00:08:41,061
You got to tell me
it don't make any difference!

68
00:08:41,854 --> 00:08:43,730
For heaven's sake, tell him.

69
00:08:43,898 --> 00:08:45,982
It... It don't make any difference.

70
00:09:09,257 --> 00:09:12,133
That guy's dead.
You'd better believe it.

71
00:09:12,301 --> 00:09:13,385
I believe it, all right.

72
00:09:13,553 --> 00:09:16,721
But if he jumps up again,
I'm getting the hell out of here.

73
00:09:16,889 --> 00:09:20,809
- What a routine he went through.
- Somebody ought to cover him up.

74
00:09:21,686 --> 00:09:24,104
What are you looking at?
All I got is this sweater.

75
00:09:24,272 --> 00:09:26,273
I got a blanket in the truck.

76
00:09:26,440 --> 00:09:29,067
Do you think
there was anything in all that?

77
00:09:29,235 --> 00:09:31,403
He was just raving. He flipped.

78
00:09:31,571 --> 00:09:35,031
Hey. This must...
This must be the police.

79
00:09:35,199 --> 00:09:37,659
Think we ought to tell them
what he said?

80
00:09:37,827 --> 00:09:40,662
Don't say anything
or we'll be here all day.

81
00:09:40,830 --> 00:09:43,540
We got to be in Vegas this afternoon.

82
00:09:43,708 --> 00:09:45,667
I got a van of furniture to get to Yuma.

83
00:09:45,835 --> 00:09:48,503
My wife and I are on
our second honeymoon.

84
00:09:48,671 --> 00:09:52,757
My wife's up there with her mother.
We're on our way to Lake Mead.

85
00:09:52,925 --> 00:09:55,927
What's to argue about? Just clam up.
Don't say nothing.

86
00:09:56,095 --> 00:09:58,013
This way, we get out of here.

87
00:09:59,515 --> 00:10:02,267
Are you a police officer?

88
00:10:10,276 --> 00:10:11,276
Yep!

89
00:10:16,741 --> 00:10:19,534
- How long ago did this happen?
- A few minutes ago.

90
00:10:19,702 --> 00:10:22,037
About five minutes ago.

91
00:10:22,204 --> 00:10:25,206
- Any of you actually see it happen?
- Well, uh...

92
00:10:25,374 --> 00:10:28,543
- He passed me on the curve...
- Did anybody actually see it?

93
00:10:28,711 --> 00:10:31,254
He was passing me
when he sailed right out there.

94
00:10:31,422 --> 00:10:34,215
- Right over there, up there.
- Who was the first down here?

95
00:10:34,383 --> 00:10:37,010
We all went down.

96
00:10:37,178 --> 00:10:38,887
Was he dead?

97
00:10:39,055 --> 00:10:40,722
Was he already dead?

98
00:10:42,141 --> 00:10:44,934
I said, "Was he already dead
when you got down here?"

99
00:10:46,145 --> 00:10:47,312
Practically.

100
00:10:48,230 --> 00:10:50,899
He was still alive.
Did he say anything?

101
00:10:53,319 --> 00:10:56,946
- Did he say anything before he died?
- What about?

102
00:10:57,114 --> 00:10:58,782
What do you mean, "what about?"

103
00:10:58,949 --> 00:11:01,785
Did he say anything
or didn't he say anything?

104
00:11:06,582 --> 00:11:09,376
- He was raving, Officer.
- Raving? What about?

105
00:11:09,543 --> 00:11:13,254
Well, he said...
What he said was sort of...

106
00:11:13,422 --> 00:11:14,756
Embarrassing.

107
00:11:14,924 --> 00:11:16,925
What was? Come on.

108
00:11:18,177 --> 00:11:20,428
He thought
that this fellow was his aunt.

109
00:11:21,013 --> 00:11:23,223
- His aunt?
- Yeah. His Aunt Belle.

110
00:11:23,391 --> 00:11:25,266
Must have had an aunt
named Aunt Belle.

111
00:11:25,810 --> 00:11:26,935
All right!

112
00:11:27,853 --> 00:11:30,939
Did he make any kind of statement?
Any last messages?

113
00:11:31,107 --> 00:11:34,067
He didn't make that clear at all.

114
00:11:34,235 --> 00:11:36,736
He didn't make anything clear.
Can we get going?

115
00:11:36,904 --> 00:11:38,738
Just a minute.

116
00:11:38,906 --> 00:11:41,282
I'll get your names
and where you can be reached.

117
00:11:41,450 --> 00:11:43,993
We're on our honeymoon.
We don't know where we'll be.

118
00:11:44,161 --> 00:11:45,412
We can't stick around.

119
00:11:45,579 --> 00:11:49,541
We're due in Las Vegas.
We don't know how long we'll stay there.

120
00:11:49,709 --> 00:11:53,044
I got a van of furniture to get to Yuma
before I get back to...

121
00:11:53,212 --> 00:11:55,088
We stopped to see if we could help.

122
00:11:55,256 --> 00:11:57,298
We was too late. Let us go, okay?

123
00:11:57,466 --> 00:12:00,218
We'll hold services for him later.
We got our lives to live.

124
00:12:00,386 --> 00:12:03,346
- We ain't had breakfast yet.
- All right.

125
00:12:03,514 --> 00:12:05,807
I'll have to get your name, anyway.

126
00:12:07,017 --> 00:12:08,143
Hold it.

127
00:12:10,104 --> 00:12:11,312
Me?

128
00:12:12,189 --> 00:12:15,734
- Why?
- In case the coroner wants a statement.

129
00:12:17,027 --> 00:12:20,321
J. Russell Finch,
2790 Penrose Boulevard, Fresno.

130
00:12:20,489 --> 00:12:24,159
I won't be home for a few weeks
but you can get me through my office.

131
00:12:24,326 --> 00:12:26,828
- What'd you say?
- Where is your office?

132
00:12:26,996 --> 00:12:30,790
Pacific Edible Seaweed Company
and it's in Fresno.

133
00:12:30,958 --> 00:12:33,543
- You can call my secretary.
- Ambulance is on its way.

134
00:12:33,711 --> 00:12:34,669
Yeah.

135
00:12:34,837 --> 00:12:36,379
- Is he dead?
- Yeah.

136
00:12:37,965 --> 00:12:40,341
We'd better shift those cars.
They're on the curb.

137
00:12:40,509 --> 00:12:42,844
That's all we can get from this group.

138
00:12:43,012 --> 00:12:44,804
Thank you, gentlemen.

139
00:12:44,972 --> 00:12:46,181
Thanks.

140
00:12:53,355 --> 00:12:55,231
Well...

141
00:12:55,399 --> 00:12:57,942
There's an unexpected twist for you.

142
00:12:58,110 --> 00:13:00,653
They're not going to like this
down at Santa Rosita.

143
00:13:01,363 --> 00:13:03,698
- Culpeper's going to scream.
- Yeah.

144
00:13:03,866 --> 00:13:06,868
- We better get our story straight if...
- What story?

145
00:13:07,036 --> 00:13:09,454
He woke up as usual.
He started driving his car.

146
00:13:09,622 --> 00:13:11,080
He stopped for breakfast.

147
00:13:11,248 --> 00:13:13,833
He went to the gents' room,
climbed out the back window.

148
00:13:14,001 --> 00:13:17,796
So what? Even Culpeper can't say
we should've been in there with him.

149
00:13:17,963 --> 00:13:20,924
What got me is the way
he went sailing out there.

150
00:13:22,176 --> 00:13:25,303
If I have to climb much more,
I'll be laying there with him.

151
00:13:25,471 --> 00:13:26,471
Poor soul.

152
00:13:33,395 --> 00:13:35,104
Uh...

153
00:13:35,564 --> 00:13:38,066
Melville, what happened?

154
00:13:38,234 --> 00:13:41,486
We couldn't do anything for him.
Nothing we could do. Come on.

155
00:13:41,654 --> 00:13:42,904
Well?

156
00:13:45,783 --> 00:13:47,033
Uh...

157
00:13:47,201 --> 00:13:49,911
- It was a terrible thing.
- Russell, I feel sick.

158
00:13:50,079 --> 00:13:51,538
Take it easy. These things happen.

159
00:13:51,705 --> 00:13:54,374
What kind of attitude is that,
"these things happen"?

160
00:13:54,542 --> 00:13:57,627
They only happen because this country
is full of people...

161
00:13:57,795 --> 00:14:00,588
...who, when things happen,
just say, "These things happen. "

162
00:14:00,756 --> 00:14:04,425
- And that's why they happen!
- Let's try not to get upset.

163
00:14:04,593 --> 00:14:05,927
Come on.

164
00:14:06,095 --> 00:14:08,304
We got to have control
of what happens to us.

165
00:14:08,472 --> 00:14:11,182
If we left it up to you,
we'd never hear the last of it.

166
00:14:11,350 --> 00:14:13,935
You're right.

167
00:14:18,899 --> 00:14:22,944
Do you know what those half-wit
morons up in Sacramento do about it?

168
00:14:23,112 --> 00:14:26,489
They just sit there with their big feet
up on their big desk...

169
00:14:26,657 --> 00:14:31,452
...milking 15 million people of...
- Listen, I want to say something.

170
00:14:31,620 --> 00:14:33,955
I'm sorry to interrupt,
but I've got to say something.

171
00:14:34,123 --> 00:14:37,125
- What are you looking at?
- I'm watching something.

172
00:14:37,293 --> 00:14:39,294
Benjy, turn around, sit still.

173
00:14:39,461 --> 00:14:43,089
- Play it straight.
- They're not kiddin'. They went for it.

174
00:14:43,257 --> 00:14:45,466
Yeah? What are you going to do now?

175
00:14:45,634 --> 00:14:49,220
I want you to tell me everything
that man told you, word for word.

176
00:14:49,388 --> 00:14:50,305
Don't leave out anything.

177
00:14:50,472 --> 00:14:52,348
But do you think he really meant it?

178
00:14:54,643 --> 00:14:58,563
Monica, I don't know about anybody else,
but some of them believed it.

179
00:14:58,731 --> 00:15:01,774
Like those two back there.
Don't look over there!

180
00:15:01,942 --> 00:15:05,278
I know where it is. It's under a big W.
That's what he said.

181
00:15:05,446 --> 00:15:07,739
Like a windmill or a waterfall
or something.

182
00:15:07,907 --> 00:15:10,617
I hope it's not under a waterfall.

183
00:15:10,784 --> 00:15:13,286
Think of something that starts with a W.

184
00:15:13,454 --> 00:15:15,997
Wealth. Which.

185
00:15:16,749 --> 00:15:18,249
Let's see. Where.

186
00:15:18,417 --> 00:15:20,835
Work. That's it.
I got to work on where it is.

187
00:15:21,003 --> 00:15:25,256
One thing Dr. Carroll said was Russell
was to have no undue excitement...

188
00:15:25,424 --> 00:15:27,008
...for at least two weeks
because of his condition.

189
00:15:27,176 --> 00:15:28,968
- But...
- That's why we came on this trip...

190
00:15:29,136 --> 00:15:31,846
...so Russell could relax.
You should have told the police.

191
00:15:32,014 --> 00:15:34,599
You keep saying that.
What's the police got to do with it?

192
00:15:34,767 --> 00:15:37,936
I think the police were chasing him.
They drove up so fast.

193
00:15:38,103 --> 00:15:41,022
Why shouldn't they've been chasing him?
He was speeding.

194
00:15:41,190 --> 00:15:43,024
I'm only thinking
of Russell's condition.

195
00:15:43,192 --> 00:15:47,695
You mean his financial condition.
That's the only condition he has.

196
00:15:47,863 --> 00:15:51,366
Do you know why your husband
had a nervous breakdown?

197
00:15:51,533 --> 00:15:56,162
It's because he has sunk $40,000,
including $15,000 of my money...

198
00:15:56,330 --> 00:15:59,749
...into a company that makes
seaweed for people to eat.

199
00:15:59,917 --> 00:16:03,086
Not only does nobody like it,
it costs $4 a can.

200
00:16:03,253 --> 00:16:05,380
- Yeah, but...
- "Yeah, but," what?

201
00:16:05,547 --> 00:16:07,548
Most people like it and I like it.

202
00:16:07,716 --> 00:16:09,926
I'm working hard,
trying to keep the costs down.

203
00:16:10,094 --> 00:16:12,220
You were working hard
to keep the costs down...

204
00:16:12,388 --> 00:16:15,556
...the day you ran
into the street screaming.

205
00:16:15,724 --> 00:16:18,977
- Mother!
- Emmeline, shut up! And you, too!

206
00:16:19,144 --> 00:16:21,562
Maybe he was playing
a trick on everybody.

207
00:16:21,730 --> 00:16:24,357
Did you think about that?
He might have been a practical joker.

208
00:16:24,525 --> 00:16:27,777
Oh... Monica! Practical!

209
00:16:27,945 --> 00:16:31,572
What kind of man is going to play a
practical joke on complete strangers...

210
00:16:31,740 --> 00:16:34,325
...with every bone in his body broken?

211
00:16:34,493 --> 00:16:37,578
- Watch! Watchtower!
- No.

212
00:16:37,746 --> 00:16:38,788
- Wall...
- No.

213
00:16:38,956 --> 00:16:40,707
- Walnut tree.
- No, no!

214
00:16:40,874 --> 00:16:42,000
- Walnuts.
- No!

215
00:16:42,167 --> 00:16:43,751
- In bags.
- No!

216
00:16:44,753 --> 00:16:48,131
Why are we doing only 35?
Step on it! See what happens.

217
00:16:48,298 --> 00:16:50,299
- Mother!
- They'll see what we're doing.

218
00:16:50,467 --> 00:16:52,427
Go ahead and try it.
What've you got to lose?

219
00:16:52,594 --> 00:16:54,929
Mother, he's not that good a driver.

220
00:17:03,772 --> 00:17:05,940
- Uh-huh.
- A-ha!

221
00:17:06,108 --> 00:17:08,317
Going to leave the big boy behind?

222
00:17:28,130 --> 00:17:30,381
What are you doing?
Why are we slowing down?

223
00:17:30,549 --> 00:17:32,800
It's no use.
We can't lose them this way.

224
00:17:32,968 --> 00:17:35,595
The inside of my stomach...

225
00:17:50,611 --> 00:17:52,987
What's that idiot in the truck doing?

226
00:17:53,155 --> 00:17:55,323
What's he doin' back there?

227
00:17:56,158 --> 00:17:58,326
I bet he's running out of gas. Good!

228
00:18:47,501 --> 00:18:49,293
What happened to you?

229
00:18:49,461 --> 00:18:52,296
- Having trouble with your engine?
- Run out of gas?

230
00:18:52,464 --> 00:18:56,717
- What, you bend your tailpipe?
- No. It was just one of my tires.

231
00:18:56,885 --> 00:18:58,511
I thought...

232
00:18:58,679 --> 00:19:01,389
Shucks! Okay, so I was trying to...

233
00:19:01,557 --> 00:19:02,473
Rats.

234
00:19:02,641 --> 00:19:05,101
This whole thing...
I think we're making a big mistake.

235
00:19:05,269 --> 00:19:07,478
- I absolutely agree.
- So?

236
00:19:07,646 --> 00:19:09,730
We're being silly
running around like this.

237
00:19:09,898 --> 00:19:12,316
- Sure. We're getting nowhere.
- By george, he's right.

238
00:19:12,484 --> 00:19:15,570
Let's do something sensible.
Let's just discuss this thing...

239
00:19:15,737 --> 00:19:18,197
...and reason something out.
- I'm with you.

240
00:19:18,365 --> 00:19:21,284
And we can come to some conclusion
like intelligent people.

241
00:19:21,451 --> 00:19:23,244
Let's do that: What he said.

242
00:19:23,412 --> 00:19:26,539
Yeah. That way nobody will have an
advantage on one another, right?

243
00:19:26,707 --> 00:19:27,874
It's fair.

244
00:19:28,041 --> 00:19:29,709
We'd better get the cars off that curve.

245
00:19:29,877 --> 00:19:32,753
Let's not talk here, but over there.
There's plenty of room.

246
00:19:32,921 --> 00:19:34,422
Fine, see you over there.

247
00:19:34,590 --> 00:19:36,716
Over there.

248
00:19:39,428 --> 00:19:41,053
You're through to Homicide.

249
00:19:43,223 --> 00:19:45,266
Santa Rosita Police Station...

250
00:19:45,726 --> 00:19:47,018
...Detective Division.

251
00:19:47,186 --> 00:19:50,438
I'm connecting you now.
Santa Rosita Police Station.

252
00:19:50,606 --> 00:19:52,440
Detective Division. Matthews.

253
00:19:53,025 --> 00:19:56,611
No, Sheriff, the Chief isn't here.
He's a little late this morning.

254
00:19:56,778 --> 00:19:59,113
I'll stay late after school. Who is it?

255
00:19:59,281 --> 00:20:01,574
- Sheriff, Crockett County.
- Who?

256
00:20:01,742 --> 00:20:04,452
- That's where the Smiler is.
- I wonder if anything happened.

257
00:20:04,620 --> 00:20:07,205
Gertie, will you put
that call through here?

258
00:20:07,372 --> 00:20:09,415
How about some coffee, Schwartz?

259
00:20:17,591 --> 00:20:19,508
Hello, Sheriff. Culpeper.

260
00:20:19,676 --> 00:20:21,719
What'd he do, make a break?
What happened?

261
00:20:21,887 --> 00:20:23,804
Afraid I got some bad news.

262
00:20:23,972 --> 00:20:27,058
- Grogan's cashed in his chips.
- He what?

263
00:20:27,226 --> 00:20:30,269
He crashed his car
about 20 minutes ago.

264
00:20:30,437 --> 00:20:32,521
He was making a break, all right.

265
00:20:33,440 --> 00:20:36,275
How did it happen?
Where did it happen?

266
00:20:37,819 --> 00:20:42,615
On 39, about 18 miles east
of Danby Junction.

267
00:20:42,783 --> 00:20:46,994
- Nine miles west of Valley Center.
- Were there any witnesses?

268
00:20:47,162 --> 00:20:49,705
A few people went down
to see if they could help.

269
00:20:49,873 --> 00:20:53,000
- Was he killed outright?
- I don't know, but I can find out.

270
00:20:53,168 --> 00:20:54,961
Do that. See what they said.

271
00:20:55,128 --> 00:20:57,004
Thanks very much, Sheriff.

272
00:21:02,010 --> 00:21:03,344
Well...

273
00:21:03,512 --> 00:21:06,347
It's a great way to start the day.

274
00:21:06,515 --> 00:21:09,600
You wait for 15 years
to solve a really important case...

275
00:21:09,768 --> 00:21:11,102
...and just when you...

276
00:21:15,190 --> 00:21:17,608
It's all right, Chief.
I'll get it for you.

277
00:21:21,196 --> 00:21:22,571
He did it again.

278
00:21:40,966 --> 00:21:43,175
Get that fella's number!
Get his number!

279
00:21:43,343 --> 00:21:45,720
Get that fella's number!
Get his number!

280
00:21:51,351 --> 00:21:55,563
Item: One large furniture
van. Item: One red Volkswagen.

281
00:21:55,731 --> 00:21:57,940
That's them. Call in.

282
00:21:58,692 --> 00:22:00,609
2-1-6-2, 2-1-5-8.

283
00:22:00,777 --> 00:22:03,404
We just made all four of them
parked alongside the road.

284
00:22:03,572 --> 00:22:06,073
They're standing there talking. Over.

285
00:22:06,241 --> 00:22:10,328
Sammy, let that ambulance
go. And stay by the radio.

286
00:22:10,495 --> 00:22:15,082
The man said there was a certain amount
of money buried in this park.

287
00:22:15,250 --> 00:22:16,292
Under a big W.

288
00:22:16,460 --> 00:22:18,002
What is a big W?

289
00:22:18,170 --> 00:22:19,920
We find out, we'll send you a wire.

290
00:22:21,590 --> 00:22:24,884
It's only a possibility
that this man was telling the truth.

291
00:22:25,052 --> 00:22:30,431
If it was the truth, then it is a fact
this place is almost 200 miles away.

292
00:22:30,599 --> 00:22:32,892
I suggest we quietly get
into our cars...

293
00:22:33,060 --> 00:22:37,146
...and drive down there
at a safe, sound speed...

294
00:22:37,314 --> 00:22:39,690
...keeping in sight of each other.

295
00:22:39,858 --> 00:22:43,652
When we get there, we dig up the money,
providing there is money...

296
00:22:43,820 --> 00:22:47,114
...and if we do find it, we share it
amongst us in a simple manner.

297
00:22:47,282 --> 00:22:48,908
He's got a point. He's got something.

298
00:22:49,076 --> 00:22:52,119
- We should go straight to the police.
- The police? Why?

299
00:22:52,287 --> 00:22:56,374
It's all right, she's with us.
What's this "fair shares for everybody"?

300
00:22:56,541 --> 00:23:01,212
We arrived in four vehicles. I think
we should split it up in four quarters.

301
00:23:02,506 --> 00:23:05,007
Four quarters?
What are you talking about? Quarters?

302
00:23:05,175 --> 00:23:08,552
You mean you three each get a quarter
and we have to split a quarter?

303
00:23:08,720 --> 00:23:11,055
- That's right.
- What are you trying to pull?

304
00:23:11,223 --> 00:23:14,225
- Seems fair to me.
- Naturally, it's fair to you.

305
00:23:14,393 --> 00:23:20,106
- It just cheats us, that's all.
- $350,000 divided by four is...

306
00:23:20,273 --> 00:23:22,858
...let's say, $87,500.

307
00:23:23,026 --> 00:23:24,527
That's what it is.

308
00:23:24,694 --> 00:23:28,072
The three of you get $87,500
and Benjy and I have to split.

309
00:23:28,240 --> 00:23:31,534
There was five of us down at the wreck.
We should split it five ways.

310
00:23:31,701 --> 00:23:32,743
He's right. We should.

311
00:23:32,911 --> 00:23:35,496
I'm perfectly willing to discuss it
in a five-way manner.

312
00:23:35,664 --> 00:23:38,332
We can discuss it in a five-way manner,
five shares...

313
00:23:38,500 --> 00:23:40,668
...each share would be $70,000...

314
00:23:40,836 --> 00:23:42,461
$70,000?

315
00:23:42,629 --> 00:23:43,671
Holy mackerel!

316
00:23:43,839 --> 00:23:47,842
You realize how many loads
I'd have to haul from Modesto to Yuma...

317
00:23:48,009 --> 00:23:49,427
You're overlooking one thing.

318
00:23:49,594 --> 00:23:51,595
- We're overlooking...
- What little thing?

319
00:23:51,763 --> 00:23:54,014
- What little thing?
- We can all count.

320
00:23:54,182 --> 00:23:56,600
- There were eight of us.
- There were eight of us.

321
00:23:56,768 --> 00:23:59,437
Speaking for my wife and myself,
we'd be just as happy...

322
00:23:59,604 --> 00:24:03,149
Happy with two-eighths instead
of a quarter? Awfully big of you.

323
00:24:03,316 --> 00:24:06,235
Wait a minute, hold it.
Put it back the way it was before.

324
00:24:06,403 --> 00:24:08,612
Either one quarter for each car,

325
00:24:08,780 --> 00:24:11,740
including the van,
or one fifth for each guy.

326
00:24:11,908 --> 00:24:16,454
- Because this old bag has to stick...
- How dare you!

327
00:24:16,621 --> 00:24:21,125
Chief, we got a situation here
that is absolutely incredible.

328
00:24:21,293 --> 00:24:24,378
- Look, Smiler Grogan... Remember him?
- Yes.

329
00:24:24,546 --> 00:24:27,214
Smiler Grogan spent the night here, see?

330
00:24:27,382 --> 00:24:29,467
Made his break this morning.

331
00:24:29,634 --> 00:24:34,013
He drove up this way, got to here,
crashed and killed himself.

332
00:24:34,181 --> 00:24:37,558
But before he died,
some people stopped to help him.

333
00:24:37,726 --> 00:24:40,853
They are now stopped here, talking.

334
00:24:41,021 --> 00:24:44,064
I think they're arguing about something.

335
00:24:44,232 --> 00:24:48,569
And a Crockett County unit
has got them under observation.

336
00:24:48,820 --> 00:24:51,822
We give shares to everybody
and for everything.

337
00:24:51,990 --> 00:24:53,908
Now, there are eight of us.

338
00:24:54,075 --> 00:24:56,911
There's eight shares for that.
Then there were four vehicles.

339
00:24:57,078 --> 00:25:00,247
If we give four shares for that,
that's 12 shares already.

340
00:25:00,415 --> 00:25:02,583
There were five of us
who went down to the wreck.

341
00:25:02,751 --> 00:25:04,251
We give five shares for that.

342
00:25:04,419 --> 00:25:06,128
That makes it 17, right?

343
00:25:06,296 --> 00:25:08,130
Now, 17 shares and then we add...

344
00:25:08,298 --> 00:25:11,133
...the same number of shares
as people in each vehicle.

345
00:25:11,301 --> 00:25:14,595
Three for your group, two for yours,
two for us, and one for you.

346
00:25:14,763 --> 00:25:17,264
That adds up to 25 shares.

347
00:25:17,432 --> 00:25:22,603
25 into 350,000 is $14,000 per share.

348
00:25:22,771 --> 00:25:24,480
Figured like that would mean...

349
00:25:24,648 --> 00:25:27,942
...you'd get three shares for being
three people, one for the car...

350
00:25:28,109 --> 00:25:30,694
...one share for going down
and looking at the wreck...

351
00:25:30,862 --> 00:25:33,322
...and three for being
three more people in the car.

352
00:25:33,490 --> 00:25:38,410
A total of eight shares,
giving you $112,000.

353
00:25:38,578 --> 00:25:41,997
That should cover everything,
including the emancipation of women.

354
00:25:42,165 --> 00:25:43,290
Let's see now.

355
00:25:43,458 --> 00:25:46,544
I got one share for being one person...

356
00:25:46,711 --> 00:25:50,130
...one share for going down the hill,
one share for the truck...

357
00:25:50,298 --> 00:25:52,967
...one share for being a person
in the truck.

358
00:25:53,134 --> 00:25:58,597
But no matter how you figure it out, I
still don't get as much as anybody else.

359
00:25:58,765 --> 00:26:00,891
Let me explain it once more.

360
00:26:01,059 --> 00:26:06,105
Their group, they, those three of them,
they get $112,000, right?

361
00:26:06,273 --> 00:26:09,525
Those over there, them,
they get $97,000.

362
00:26:09,693 --> 00:26:12,152
We, us, we get $84,000.

363
00:26:12,320 --> 00:26:16,615
And you, by yourself,
you get $56,000...

364
00:26:16,783 --> 00:26:17,658
...alone.

365
00:26:17,826 --> 00:26:20,828
- That's tax-free money.
- What do you mean, tax-free?

366
00:26:20,996 --> 00:26:24,957
If we go down to this park
and we uncover the money...

367
00:26:25,125 --> 00:26:27,835
I'm sure he's not going
to declare anything.

368
00:26:28,003 --> 00:26:29,837
I know he's not going
to declare anything.

369
00:26:30,005 --> 00:26:34,508
- I'm not going to declare...
- What are you talking about, declare it?

370
00:26:34,676 --> 00:26:37,261
I mean, it's like non-taxable income.

371
00:26:37,429 --> 00:26:39,555
It's like a gift.

372
00:26:39,723 --> 00:26:43,058
If we find the money,
we still have to report the taxes.

373
00:26:43,226 --> 00:26:46,020
Otherwise, it's like stealing
from the government.

374
00:26:46,187 --> 00:26:48,355
You explain it to him, please.

375
00:26:49,149 --> 00:26:50,733
Who me?

376
00:26:50,900 --> 00:26:54,653
If we find the money,
there may not be taxes to pay on it...

377
00:26:54,821 --> 00:26:56,363
...because we found it.

378
00:26:56,531 --> 00:27:00,451
- What he was trying to say is...
- Everybody has to pay taxes.

379
00:27:00,619 --> 00:27:04,830
Even businessmen that rob,
steal and cheat people every day...

380
00:27:04,998 --> 00:27:06,665
...even they have to pay taxes.

381
00:27:07,500 --> 00:27:10,461
I give up. Anybody got a better,
fairer plan, go ahead.

382
00:27:10,629 --> 00:27:14,506
There were eight of us there,
so that simply means eight shares.

383
00:27:14,674 --> 00:27:17,468
- Three for us, two for you...
- This is hopeless.

384
00:27:17,636 --> 00:27:20,721
We'll get no place if we continue
listening to this old bag.

385
00:27:20,889 --> 00:27:24,475
Lady, you trying to split us up
so every man's for himself?

386
00:27:24,643 --> 00:27:26,060
And every woman for himself?

387
00:27:26,227 --> 00:27:27,895
One more funny remark from you...

388
00:27:28,063 --> 00:27:31,065
- Let's get out of here.
- Please, don't argue anymore.

389
00:27:31,232 --> 00:27:34,526
We figured it 17 different ways.

390
00:27:34,694 --> 00:27:36,904
Every time we figured it,
it was no good.

391
00:27:37,072 --> 00:27:40,658
No matter how we figured it,
somebody didn't like it.

392
00:27:40,825 --> 00:27:44,036
Now there's only one way to figure it.

393
00:27:44,204 --> 00:27:45,913
And that is, every man...

394
00:27:46,081 --> 00:27:48,707
...including the old bag, for himself!

395
00:27:48,875 --> 00:27:51,919
- Good luck and may the best man win!
- Right!

396
00:27:52,087 --> 00:27:56,090
Except you, lady.
May you just drop dead!

397
00:27:56,257 --> 00:27:58,425
All right. We all agree on that.

398
00:27:58,593 --> 00:28:03,597
Let's be sensible about this thing.
There's money in this for all of us.

399
00:28:03,765 --> 00:28:06,934
There's enough for you.
There's enough for you...

400
00:28:07,727 --> 00:28:09,645
...for me...

401
00:28:09,813 --> 00:28:11,939
...and for you...

402
00:28:12,107 --> 00:28:13,774
...and there's enough for...

403
00:28:15,360 --> 00:28:17,027
Melville, my shoe!

404
00:28:17,195 --> 00:28:18,946
Get in the car!

405
00:28:47,559 --> 00:28:52,062
2-1-5-8, 2-1-6-2, four cars under
observation are passing this checkpoint.

406
00:28:52,230 --> 00:28:54,064
Lead car is Plymouth station wagon.

407
00:28:54,232 --> 00:28:56,066
Next, the Ford van, the Volkswagen...

408
00:28:56,234 --> 00:28:58,986
...and the Chrysler Imperial
convertible, all doing about 50.

409
00:28:59,154 --> 00:29:01,196
Yep, they're on their way.

410
00:29:01,364 --> 00:29:03,240
All traveling
in the same direction?

411
00:29:03,408 --> 00:29:05,033
Right. According to my boys...

412
00:29:05,201 --> 00:29:08,078
...they're all
on reckless driving charges already.

413
00:29:08,246 --> 00:29:12,833
None of those people must suspect
that anybody's interested in them.

414
00:29:13,001 --> 00:29:15,377
Now, Sheriff,
will you get on to Capt. Hardesty...

415
00:29:15,545 --> 00:29:17,963
...and see how many helicopters
he can let us have?

416
00:29:18,131 --> 00:29:21,633
I'll see what we can do
and I'll call you back.

417
00:29:22,927 --> 00:29:26,680
Now, where have I always told you
that the Smiler hid the dough?

418
00:29:26,848 --> 00:29:28,766
- I know.
- Where?

419
00:29:28,933 --> 00:29:32,352
- Right there.
- That's right, yeah.

420
00:29:32,520 --> 00:29:35,355
If these merrymakers
decide to go for it...

421
00:29:35,523 --> 00:29:38,400
...they'll go to the crossroads
and turn south.

422
00:29:39,194 --> 00:29:41,862
But why did Smiler head east
when he made his break...

423
00:29:42,030 --> 00:29:44,198
...if the money is down here somewhere?

424
00:29:44,365 --> 00:29:45,574
Oh!

425
00:29:45,742 --> 00:29:50,037
Aloysius, the guy is just being clever.
You can't...

426
00:29:50,205 --> 00:29:52,289
5 will get you 10...

427
00:29:52,457 --> 00:29:56,376
...they turn south at the crossroads.
- You got yourself a bet.

428
00:30:10,558 --> 00:30:12,726
"Mount Shasta National Forest. "
Are we near...

429
00:30:12,894 --> 00:30:15,521
That's on the top!
Look down near the bottom.

430
00:30:16,856 --> 00:30:20,150
- Are we near Oregon?
- That's 700 miles from here.

431
00:30:34,332 --> 00:30:36,124
Don't pass it!

432
00:30:43,007 --> 00:30:45,050
You'll lose your license.

433
00:30:49,764 --> 00:30:52,975
We've got the Imperial
and we're running last?

434
00:30:53,142 --> 00:30:55,143
I can't pass them on the curves.

435
00:30:55,311 --> 00:30:57,938
Go on. Go ahead. Look, there's a space!

436
00:30:58,106 --> 00:31:01,024
You waiting for an engraved invitation?

437
00:31:01,192 --> 00:31:03,652
Get over!

438
00:31:03,820 --> 00:31:05,779
Get over to the side
where you belong!

439
00:32:00,501 --> 00:32:02,753
I said it before and I'll say it again.

440
00:32:02,921 --> 00:32:05,339
I didn't want to move to California.

441
00:32:15,850 --> 00:32:18,644
- Did you find it yet?
- I can't find it anywhere.

442
00:32:18,811 --> 00:32:20,354
Take the wheel. Give me the map.

443
00:32:20,521 --> 00:32:22,397
Take the wheel! Give me the map.

444
00:32:23,274 --> 00:32:25,817
It must be here.
Right over here. Valley Center!

445
00:32:25,985 --> 00:32:27,110
It's right here.

446
00:32:27,278 --> 00:32:28,862
There's an airfield not far...

447
00:32:29,030 --> 00:32:31,698
Get it off your face!

448
00:32:34,285 --> 00:32:36,787
- Get it off me!
- Don't go in there!

449
00:32:36,955 --> 00:32:39,206
Swing over! Watch out!

450
00:32:43,836 --> 00:32:45,837
- Take it off.
- Get it off!

451
00:32:46,005 --> 00:32:47,589
I've had enough.

452
00:33:02,981 --> 00:33:05,232
- They're going to hire airplanes.
- Never mind. Go!

453
00:33:05,400 --> 00:33:08,694
- But they'll be there hours before...
- I said never mind. Let's go!

454
00:33:08,861 --> 00:33:10,988
Nobody's getting me up in the air.

455
00:33:23,918 --> 00:33:27,504
I wanted to be reasonable,
give them reasonable shares.

456
00:33:27,672 --> 00:33:30,257
No. They wanted every man for himself.

457
00:33:30,425 --> 00:33:33,343
I'm going to show them
what kind of man they're dealing with.

458
00:33:42,020 --> 00:33:44,813
It's stalled, Benjy.
We got dust in the carburetor.

459
00:33:51,738 --> 00:33:55,282
When the people who own this see this,
I sure hate to think...

460
00:33:55,450 --> 00:33:57,576
Never mind.

461
00:33:57,744 --> 00:33:58,744
Here's the bike.

462
00:33:58,911 --> 00:34:01,788
Get to the nearest phone
and hire the best car you can find.

463
00:34:01,956 --> 00:34:06,793
But this is a girl's bike.
This is for a little girl.

464
00:34:06,961 --> 00:34:09,755
I've got to get this stuff back
so I can lock up the van.

465
00:34:09,922 --> 00:34:12,674
We'll put everything away.
Will you get going? Hurry.

466
00:34:13,301 --> 00:34:14,885
Okay.

467
00:34:15,720 --> 00:34:17,179
I got to admit...

468
00:34:18,639 --> 00:34:20,640
...I feel kind of silly.

469
00:34:20,808 --> 00:34:22,559
You know what I mean?

470
00:34:31,319 --> 00:34:33,695
Will you take us or won't you?

471
00:34:33,863 --> 00:34:36,156
For $250, I guess I will.

472
00:34:36,324 --> 00:34:40,077
You take care of the plane.
We'll leave our car here till tomorrow.

473
00:34:40,244 --> 00:34:42,412
- I'll give you a check.
- Check?

474
00:34:42,580 --> 00:34:44,998
Traveler's check from
the Bank of America. Don't worry.

475
00:34:45,166 --> 00:34:47,584
- Oh, boy.
- Hey!

476
00:34:47,752 --> 00:34:50,212
Are you a pilot?
Is there a plane around?

477
00:34:50,379 --> 00:34:51,379
Right both times.

478
00:34:51,547 --> 00:34:53,632
Where's an airplane? I don't see any.

479
00:34:53,800 --> 00:34:55,675
There's only one. We've chartered it.

480
00:34:55,843 --> 00:34:58,512
- So you and your friend...
- Did you make a deal with them?

481
00:34:58,679 --> 00:35:01,848
- Right.
- Where can we charter another plane?

482
00:35:02,016 --> 00:35:04,726
- Nearest place is North Valley.
- Where's that?

483
00:35:04,894 --> 00:35:08,647
Other side of Valley Center,
about 12 miles, 15 miles.

484
00:35:08,815 --> 00:35:11,733
- Excuse us.
- Filibuster, filibuster.

485
00:35:11,901 --> 00:35:13,985
You can stick around
and watch us take off.

486
00:35:14,153 --> 00:35:16,571
Listen, dentist. I hate dentists.

487
00:35:16,739 --> 00:35:20,659
I hate you so much, I'm not able to tell
you how much in front of your wife.

488
00:35:20,827 --> 00:35:22,577
Vice versa.

489
00:35:22,745 --> 00:35:26,790
Come on over here! Come on!

490
00:35:38,469 --> 00:35:39,636
Good morning.

491
00:35:39,804 --> 00:35:41,805
- Good morning.
- Had an accident?

492
00:35:41,973 --> 00:35:44,766
- Anyone hurt?
- No, but we've got to get to a phone.

493
00:35:44,934 --> 00:35:47,102
Can you give us a lift?

494
00:35:47,270 --> 00:35:50,188
Of course, I should be
absolutely delighted.

495
00:35:51,732 --> 00:35:54,818
Upsy-daisy. I'm afraid you
caught me on the hub there.

496
00:35:54,986 --> 00:35:57,362
Madam, do be careful.
I have some cactus specimens...

497
00:35:57,530 --> 00:36:00,782
- Oh!
- I'm most frightfully sorry.

498
00:36:00,950 --> 00:36:04,744
I've been gathering some samples
of desert flora.

499
00:36:04,912 --> 00:36:06,413
Where shall I put this?

500
00:36:07,748 --> 00:36:08,999
Boy.

501
00:36:10,668 --> 00:36:12,961
Good morning.

502
00:36:13,129 --> 00:36:16,131
It certainly is. We're in a hurry.
We've got to get to a phone.

503
00:36:16,299 --> 00:36:18,341
Of course, with pleasure.

504
00:36:18,509 --> 00:36:21,636
Jolly nasty accident there.
Jolly lucky nobody was hurt.

505
00:36:21,804 --> 00:36:25,140
Where did you get that funny accent?
Are you from Harvard or something?

506
00:36:25,308 --> 00:36:27,976
Harvard? Rather not. I'm English.

507
00:36:28,144 --> 00:36:29,853
Sounds so foreign.

508
00:36:30,021 --> 00:36:32,814
Really? I say,
we haven't introduced ourselves.

509
00:36:32,982 --> 00:36:35,442
My name is Algernon Hawthorne...
Col. Hawthorne.

510
00:36:35,610 --> 00:36:38,904
- You're a colonel?
- Lieutenant colonel, actually.

511
00:36:39,071 --> 00:36:40,739
My name is Finch. This is my wife.

512
00:36:40,907 --> 00:36:43,950
This is my mother-in-law, Mrs. Marcus.

513
00:36:44,118 --> 00:36:46,661
Do stuff those in the back.

514
00:36:46,829 --> 00:36:49,039
Cactus. It's rather a hobby of mine.

515
00:36:49,207 --> 00:36:52,250
Spent the last 10 days
gathering some for my collection.

516
00:36:52,418 --> 00:36:54,544
Nothing spectacular, actually.

517
00:36:54,712 --> 00:36:58,048
Cereus echinocactus, opuntia.
That sort of thing.

518
00:36:58,216 --> 00:37:00,550
Been enjoying a spot of leave
from Vandenberg.

519
00:37:00,718 --> 00:37:03,011
- From what?
- Vandenberg.

520
00:37:03,179 --> 00:37:04,596
The missile place.

521
00:37:04,764 --> 00:37:08,141
I've been attached there
for the last 10 months. Liaison work.

522
00:37:08,309 --> 00:37:10,936
All very hush-hush and whoosh-whoosh.

523
00:37:12,480 --> 00:37:13,980
That sort of thing, you know.

524
00:37:16,317 --> 00:37:18,235
Please, will you look at the road?

525
00:37:19,278 --> 00:37:21,821
Yes. Whoosh-whoosh.

526
00:37:26,994 --> 00:37:29,496
- Don't stop! Keep moving!
- Mother!

527
00:37:29,664 --> 00:37:33,083
That big stupid lout! He ran into us.
Keep moving!

528
00:37:40,841 --> 00:37:44,803
I won't fly in this old...
Listen to it.

529
00:37:44,971 --> 00:37:46,763
Look at how it's shuddering.

530
00:37:46,931 --> 00:37:50,892
Can't we go on our second honeymoon
and forget all about this?

531
00:37:51,060 --> 00:37:54,354
Honey, please, darling.
Believe me, everything is all right.

532
00:37:54,522 --> 00:37:56,731
Do you think I'd take a chance with you

533
00:37:56,899 --> 00:37:58,817
if there was any danger
in flying this thing?

534
00:37:58,985 --> 00:38:00,944
This plane is really built.

535
00:38:01,862 --> 00:38:03,738
When was this plane built?

536
00:38:03,906 --> 00:38:06,950
1916.

537
00:38:07,118 --> 00:38:11,121
1916. These planes are tried and true.

538
00:38:11,289 --> 00:38:13,873
There's nothing experimental
about these planes.

539
00:38:14,041 --> 00:38:17,002
So, come on.
Let's have one big adventure.

540
00:38:17,169 --> 00:38:19,546
Get up there and have some fun.
Here we go.

541
00:38:24,719 --> 00:38:27,053
- That scratched the paint.
- Help!

542
00:38:47,533 --> 00:38:49,200
Haven't you got another car...

543
00:38:49,368 --> 00:38:51,911
What? All right. Thanks.

544
00:38:52,079 --> 00:38:55,582
Are you sure you can't rent us
that truck? I'll pay.

545
00:38:55,750 --> 00:38:57,500
I told you, we can't.

546
00:38:57,668 --> 00:39:00,670
This is our first week open.
How could we do without our truck?

547
00:39:00,838 --> 00:39:02,630
We're in business.

548
00:39:02,798 --> 00:39:06,176
We'll have to speak to the Englishman.
If we tell him what happened...

549
00:39:06,344 --> 00:39:07,886
How can you admit we're involved...

550
00:39:08,054 --> 00:39:11,931
- He'll say he's entitled to a share.
- He would be if he drove us there.

551
00:39:12,099 --> 00:39:15,101
If we don't tell him, he won't.

552
00:39:15,936 --> 00:39:18,063
You're such a genius.

553
00:39:18,606 --> 00:39:20,273
Listen! Only 10 percent!

554
00:39:20,441 --> 00:39:22,817
There's no reason
he should expect any more!

555
00:39:35,790 --> 00:39:38,541
Thanks for stopping.
Can you give me a lift?

556
00:39:39,502 --> 00:39:42,712
What's with the kiddy bicycle?
Are you some kind of a nut?

557
00:39:42,880 --> 00:39:46,091
No. I had an accident.
I got to get to Santa Rosita fast.

558
00:39:46,258 --> 00:39:48,676
Can't help you.
I'm turning off a little way up.

559
00:39:48,844 --> 00:39:50,970
Wait, let me think.

560
00:39:51,138 --> 00:39:54,599
I got to tell somebody.
Could you spare a couple of hours?

561
00:39:54,767 --> 00:39:55,892
Couple of hours?

562
00:39:56,060 --> 00:39:59,354
You've been out in the sun too long.
You're starting to crack up.

563
00:39:59,522 --> 00:40:01,314
Wait a minute. Listen.

564
00:40:01,482 --> 00:40:03,942
Just hear me out.

565
00:40:04,110 --> 00:40:08,405
What I'm gonna tell you, you just ain't
going to believe it could've happened.

566
00:40:08,572 --> 00:40:11,074
There was an accident here
a little while back...

567
00:40:11,242 --> 00:40:15,161
...about 20 miles back.
It involved $350,000.

568
00:40:15,329 --> 00:40:17,330
Now, like I say...

569
00:40:17,498 --> 00:40:21,584
...when I tell you this, you just ain't
going to believe it could've happened.

570
00:40:22,920 --> 00:40:25,004
Try me. I'm pretty gullible.

571
00:41:05,838 --> 00:41:08,798
What bothers me is this big W.

572
00:41:08,966 --> 00:41:13,344
You sure you told me all you know?
You don't know what that guy meant?

573
00:41:13,512 --> 00:41:16,890
No, none of them know.
It's just who gets there first.

574
00:41:17,057 --> 00:41:19,267
What do you say? Is it a deal?

575
00:41:19,435 --> 00:41:22,061
Um... Deal!

576
00:41:24,523 --> 00:41:26,316
Kid, you better get
that bike out of there.

577
00:41:26,484 --> 00:41:28,902
Somebody could trip over it in the dark.

578
00:42:50,150 --> 00:42:53,486
Fellas, I'm glad you're here.
Look, I need your help.

579
00:42:53,654 --> 00:42:55,989
I had this blowout.
I think a spare's in the back.

580
00:42:56,156 --> 00:42:59,576
It may be a little flat.
Is there an airport anyplace around?

581
00:42:59,743 --> 00:43:02,495
If the spare's flat, don't fix it.
Give me a new tire.

582
00:43:02,663 --> 00:43:04,497
You ain't got a new tire, fix the spare.

583
00:43:04,665 --> 00:43:07,917
But don't look at me, move it.
You could be gassing up.

584
00:43:08,085 --> 00:43:12,130
What is it, a staring contest?
Move, move, will you? Come on!

585
00:43:12,965 --> 00:43:14,716
The pension in my grade...

586
00:43:14,883 --> 00:43:20,471
...has not been upped
one red cent since 1934.

587
00:43:20,639 --> 00:43:22,682
Now... Uh...

588
00:43:22,850 --> 00:43:25,977
If the Mayor
will get behind a resolution...

589
00:43:26,145 --> 00:43:28,688
What can I do?
I can't put any pressure on the Mayor!

590
00:43:28,856 --> 00:43:30,648
You can, Al.

591
00:43:30,816 --> 00:43:32,150
That's the whole point.

592
00:43:32,318 --> 00:43:34,527
This case,
I'll have finished by tonight.

593
00:43:34,695 --> 00:43:37,905
It's one of the biggest cases
we've ever had across our books.

594
00:43:38,073 --> 00:43:40,033
Tell the Mayor about it.

595
00:43:40,200 --> 00:43:44,704
Tell him the money is right here,
where I always said it was...

596
00:43:44,872 --> 00:43:46,581
...right in this neighborhood.

597
00:43:46,749 --> 00:43:50,376
Tell him what credit will be reflected
upon the department.

598
00:43:50,544 --> 00:43:55,006
Come on, Aloysius,
get in there and pitch for me.

599
00:43:55,174 --> 00:43:57,300
I can try.

600
00:43:58,010 --> 00:43:59,719
He'll listen to you.

601
00:43:59,887 --> 00:44:04,390
If he gets behind this,
it'll pass unanimously.

602
00:44:04,558 --> 00:44:06,225
Now, you know...

603
00:44:06,393 --> 00:44:08,436
You know, Al, I got it coming.

604
00:44:08,604 --> 00:44:11,230
I'll do everything I can.

605
00:44:11,398 --> 00:44:13,483
- You know that, don't you?
- Yes.

606
00:44:13,651 --> 00:44:16,861
There's just one other little thing...

607
00:44:17,029 --> 00:44:18,905
No. Nothing.

608
00:44:19,073 --> 00:44:20,239
Vacation.

609
00:44:20,407 --> 00:44:24,243
Once I get Smiler Grogan out of the way,
my desk is clear.

610
00:44:24,411 --> 00:44:29,874
I'd like to take a three-week vacation.
Take Ginger on a real nice holiday.

611
00:44:30,042 --> 00:44:32,710
- Is that all right with you?
- Of course it's all right.

612
00:44:32,878 --> 00:44:35,546
Thanks. I can hardly wait to tell her.

613
00:44:35,714 --> 00:44:38,549
- You won't forget about the Mayor?
- No.

614
00:44:38,717 --> 00:44:42,261
I'll do my best. I promise you that.

615
00:44:42,429 --> 00:44:45,056
Aloysius,
I'll never forget you for this.

616
00:44:45,224 --> 00:44:48,017
You know something, Al?
I got a feeling this morning...

617
00:44:48,185 --> 00:44:51,270
...that everything's coming my way.

618
00:44:59,988 --> 00:45:01,447
Sylvester!

619
00:45:07,746 --> 00:45:10,456
- Why did you do that?
- Why are you shouting?

620
00:45:10,624 --> 00:45:13,251
- Do you have to scare everybody?
- Are you crazy?

621
00:45:13,419 --> 00:45:14,627
Why didn't I think?

622
00:45:14,795 --> 00:45:16,754
We've been running around like lunatics.

623
00:45:16,922 --> 00:45:20,633
Why didn't I think about Sylvester?
He's sitting there right now.

624
00:45:20,801 --> 00:45:23,720
- He lives on Silver Strand Beach.
- I never thought of that.

625
00:45:23,887 --> 00:45:26,639
- Who on earth is Sylvester?
- My son, Emmeline's brother.

626
00:45:26,807 --> 00:45:28,224
He's a lifeguard there.

627
00:45:28,392 --> 00:45:31,894
I'm not entirely certain
that you haven't damaged this machine.

628
00:45:36,775 --> 00:45:40,278
Kid, don't mind polishing.
I got a lot of cars. Don't bother.

629
00:45:40,446 --> 00:45:42,196
You did a good job.

630
00:45:42,364 --> 00:45:44,157
Have a drink on me. Keep the change.

631
00:45:44,324 --> 00:45:46,117
I took care of your buddy.
Let me go now.

632
00:45:46,285 --> 00:45:47,160
You!

633
00:45:47,327 --> 00:45:50,621
No! It's that lunatic
who escaped from the asylum!

634
00:45:50,789 --> 00:45:53,082
Watch him! He's a homicidal maniac!

635
00:45:53,250 --> 00:45:55,334
Get on the phone, yell "Mayday. "

636
00:45:55,502 --> 00:45:57,253
Listen to me. I'm a psychiatrist.

637
00:45:57,421 --> 00:45:59,922
This man is insane! I'm not your nurse.

638
00:46:00,090 --> 00:46:01,340
He has a hate complex.

639
00:46:01,508 --> 00:46:03,593
Calm down!

640
00:46:04,136 --> 00:46:06,846
Somebody will stumble
over the bicycle in the dark, huh?

641
00:46:07,014 --> 00:46:10,850
When I finish with you, they'll be
stumbling over you in the dark!

642
00:46:11,018 --> 00:46:12,727
Get on the phone!

643
00:46:16,815 --> 00:46:18,691
Look out!

644
00:46:18,859 --> 00:46:21,360
Look, I was clowning.

645
00:46:21,528 --> 00:46:24,447
Get out of here! Sir, wait a minute.

646
00:46:24,615 --> 00:46:26,741
You've got this all...
Why don't you stop?

647
00:46:26,909 --> 00:46:28,868
I tell you. I'll kill you!

648
00:46:31,038 --> 00:46:33,164
You got this... Wait!

649
00:46:33,332 --> 00:46:35,208
Don't take it so...

650
00:46:35,375 --> 00:46:37,960
Will you stop staring and get out of...

651
00:46:38,712 --> 00:46:40,671
He's out of his head.

652
00:46:40,839 --> 00:46:43,758
- He's crazy!
- Want us to call... Ray!

653
00:46:44,760 --> 00:46:46,427
It's a brand-new pump!

654
00:46:46,595 --> 00:46:49,722
- Get out of here!
- Stop that!

655
00:46:49,890 --> 00:46:52,058
Stop that! He's crazy!

656
00:46:52,226 --> 00:46:54,101
Hey.

657
00:46:54,269 --> 00:46:56,395
Very good. Quick thinking.
I'm proud of you.

658
00:46:56,563 --> 00:46:58,356
Very good. Tie him up.

659
00:46:58,524 --> 00:47:01,359
I'll have some orderlies come by
with a straitjacket.

660
00:47:01,527 --> 00:47:04,237
- Very good. I'm proud of you.
- I never saw anything...

661
00:47:04,404 --> 00:47:06,781
- How many people has he killed?
- There'll be more.

662
00:47:06,949 --> 00:47:08,950
Tie him up for the boys
in the white jackets.

663
00:47:09,117 --> 00:47:12,036
I'm proud of you, boys.
You did a real good job.

664
00:47:12,204 --> 00:47:14,580
Look me up. I'm in the book.
Dr. Zillman.

665
00:47:16,083 --> 00:47:19,919
- Sir, we've got to get to Santa Rosita.
- I tell you, this is a club.

666
00:47:20,087 --> 00:47:22,213
We don't do charters.
Nobody here can take you.

667
00:47:22,381 --> 00:47:26,259
- Whose plane is that?
- That belongs to Mr. Tyler Fitzgerald.

668
00:47:26,426 --> 00:47:28,052
He isn't going anywhere today.

669
00:47:28,220 --> 00:47:31,889
- Is he here? Can we see him?
- Mr. Fitzgerald's in the billiard room.

670
00:47:32,057 --> 00:47:36,102
- He's asleep. Nobody can talk to him.
- Can we ask him a question?

671
00:47:36,270 --> 00:47:38,104
No, you can't.

672
00:47:38,272 --> 00:47:40,439
Hello? Wait a minute!

673
00:47:44,486 --> 00:47:47,864
Come on, Benjy.
That must be Mr. Fitzgerald over there!

674
00:47:48,031 --> 00:47:51,701
- You can't disturb Mr. Fitzgerald!
- We just want to talk to him.

675
00:47:51,869 --> 00:47:53,786
- Let him rest, please.
- Hello.

676
00:47:53,954 --> 00:47:55,037
- Sh!
- Don't shush me!

677
00:47:55,205 --> 00:47:57,123
We're trying to talk to him.

678
00:47:57,291 --> 00:47:59,208
Wake up, won't you please?

679
00:47:59,376 --> 00:48:02,336
I think he's got a cold.

680
00:48:02,504 --> 00:48:05,464
Mr. Fitzgerald, listen. Please, sir.

681
00:48:06,133 --> 00:48:09,176
We hate to disturb your sleep,
but it's an emergency.

682
00:48:09,344 --> 00:48:11,304
You've no right to crash in here.

683
00:48:13,849 --> 00:48:15,099
That's a head cold.

684
00:48:15,267 --> 00:48:17,768
Mr. Fitzgerald,
you know where Rosita Beach is?

685
00:48:17,936 --> 00:48:21,647
- Only you can get us there.
- It's a matter of life and death.

686
00:48:21,815 --> 00:48:23,566
Right, a matter of life and death.

687
00:48:23,734 --> 00:48:26,485
- It's our grandmother. She's dying.
- Who's dying?

688
00:48:26,653 --> 00:48:29,822
Our grandmother is dying
and she's sent for us.

689
00:48:30,490 --> 00:48:34,327
She's in Rosita Beach.
She's dying and we're up here.

690
00:48:34,494 --> 00:48:37,538
She'd like us with her when she goes.

691
00:48:37,706 --> 00:48:39,665
Otherwise, she won't go.

692
00:48:39,833 --> 00:48:43,169
- She'll go.
- Sir, they forced their way in here.

693
00:48:43,337 --> 00:48:46,130
No, we didn't. Let me introduce myself.

694
00:48:46,298 --> 00:48:48,174
I'm Dingy Bell. This is Benjy Benjamin.

695
00:48:48,342 --> 00:48:51,010
- How do you do?
- Don't start with that!

696
00:48:51,178 --> 00:48:54,513
Sir, we'd like you to help us out
by taking us down...

697
00:48:56,350 --> 00:48:59,185
- What's the matter?
- Wait just a minute.

698
00:49:00,729 --> 00:49:03,731
I can't see!
Something's happened to my eyes.

699
00:49:03,899 --> 00:49:05,399
I can't see!

700
00:49:05,567 --> 00:49:07,151
You can't see? He can't see.

701
00:49:07,319 --> 00:49:11,197
- Must be an eye cold.
- George, I can't see.

702
00:49:11,365 --> 00:49:14,700
- One minute, Mr. Fitzgerald.
- I can't see! George!

703
00:49:14,868 --> 00:49:16,035
George!

704
00:49:18,914 --> 00:49:19,914
Mr. Fitzgerald!

705
00:49:21,875 --> 00:49:24,335
We want to make sure
he doesn't get loose.

706
00:49:26,380 --> 00:49:28,839
I'll kill that dirty rotten bum...

707
00:49:29,007 --> 00:49:31,842
...if I get my hands on him.
What's the matter?

708
00:49:32,552 --> 00:49:33,886
How come I'm tied up like this?

709
00:49:34,054 --> 00:49:36,389
Just sit there.
Everything will be all right.

710
00:49:36,556 --> 00:49:39,058
Yeah. Friends are coming
to take care of you.

711
00:49:39,226 --> 00:49:41,352
What friends?
What are you talking about?

712
00:49:41,520 --> 00:49:43,396
Get this stuff off me. Turn me loose.

713
00:49:43,563 --> 00:49:45,398
Take it easy. You've been sick.

714
00:49:45,565 --> 00:49:49,276
Who's been sick?
And where's that bum with the glasses?

715
00:49:49,861 --> 00:49:52,822
Now just sit still,
because the doctor is going...

716
00:49:52,990 --> 00:49:56,826
What doctor? I don't know no doctor.
What are you guys, crazy or something?

717
00:49:56,994 --> 00:49:59,662
I'm warning you.
Get this stuff off me, you understand?

718
00:49:59,830 --> 00:50:02,832
- Get this stuff off me!
- Watch him, Ray, watch him!

719
00:50:03,000 --> 00:50:06,836
I'm warning you!
I'm going to have to hit you again.

720
00:50:07,004 --> 00:50:08,963
Ow!

721
00:50:09,131 --> 00:50:11,424
My arm! You broke my arm!

722
00:50:27,065 --> 00:50:30,609
You keep this up
and I'm going to get sore.

723
00:50:36,283 --> 00:50:40,453
Okay. That's the way you want it,
that's the way you're going to get it.

724
00:50:45,333 --> 00:50:48,002
- I'll kill you!
- Whoo!

725
00:50:51,048 --> 00:50:54,800
- Help! He's ruining our place!
- Come on, Ray!

726
00:51:05,479 --> 00:51:08,397
- You better get out of here, mister!
- Leave us alone!

727
00:51:14,154 --> 00:51:16,989
- Uh-huh. There you are.
- What are we going to do?

728
00:51:19,242 --> 00:51:22,328
Dr. Zillman! Dr. Zillman!

729
00:51:33,799 --> 00:51:38,719
Help! Put me down!
Put me down immediately!

730
00:51:42,474 --> 00:51:46,352
- That's the way you want it?
- Help! Help!

731
00:51:54,027 --> 00:51:55,986
- Are you all right?
- I'm fine.

732
00:52:00,700 --> 00:52:04,537
You're getting out of line. I'm not
kidding. I've had all I can take.

733
00:52:04,704 --> 00:52:07,373
Irwin, we'll have to kill him.

734
00:52:07,541 --> 00:52:08,874
- Ready?
- Ready.

735
00:52:09,042 --> 00:52:10,209
- Set?
- Set.

736
00:52:10,377 --> 00:52:11,335
Charge!

737
00:52:18,385 --> 00:52:20,970
He's going nuts! He's really nuts!

738
00:52:21,888 --> 00:52:25,015
- Go away!
- You'd better get out of here!

739
00:52:25,892 --> 00:52:27,893
I mean it, I don't want to...

740
00:52:31,648 --> 00:52:33,524
What'll we do?

741
00:52:34,276 --> 00:52:36,944
Go away!

