â™ª Bananas, I'm gonna eat

753
00:54:04,282 --> 00:54:08,452
Don't stop! Go!

754
00:54:09,371 --> 00:54:11,789
Whoo!

755
00:54:15,543 --> 00:54:16,460
He's got to be home.

756
00:54:16,628 --> 00:54:19,797
He never gets up this early.
Why doesn't he answer?

757
00:54:23,969 --> 00:54:26,679
I hope you won't mind my asking,
but what sort of chap...

758
00:54:26,846 --> 00:54:28,514
...is this brother-in-law of yours?

759
00:54:28,682 --> 00:54:30,349
He's a nut. Why?

760
00:54:30,517 --> 00:54:33,560
I hope he's nothing like
my brother-in-law. Peculiar chap.

761
00:54:33,728 --> 00:54:35,688
Secretary of a golf club
out near Pangbourne.

762
00:54:35,855 --> 00:54:37,064
So what about him?

763
00:54:37,232 --> 00:54:40,693
I was thinking that if Reggie,
my brother-in-law...

764
00:54:40,860 --> 00:54:44,196
If Reggie got hold of information
like this information...

765
00:54:44,364 --> 00:54:46,740
...it's likely that would be
the last time...

766
00:54:46,908 --> 00:54:50,536
...anyone would ever see or hear
of dear old Reggie.

767
00:54:50,704 --> 00:54:56,208
I doubt very much whether old Reggie
will be waiting for us in Santa Rosita.

768
00:54:57,460 --> 00:54:58,836
Cheers.

769
00:55:04,384 --> 00:55:06,385
Tyler! Tyler's probably
still in the shower.

770
00:55:06,553 --> 00:55:10,306
Tyler! There he is! Tyler!

771
00:55:10,473 --> 00:55:12,725
- Tyler!
- You promised!

772
00:55:12,892 --> 00:55:15,728
Hey! I'll wake him up. Tyler!

773
00:55:15,895 --> 00:55:18,522
- Tyler!
- Huh? Huh?!

774
00:55:18,690 --> 00:55:22,651
Wake up! Come on now!

775
00:55:23,320 --> 00:55:25,070
- Get out of here!
- Wait!

776
00:55:25,238 --> 00:55:26,697
Ah!

777
00:55:26,865 --> 00:55:28,240
Mr. Fitzgerald!

778
00:55:33,580 --> 00:55:36,749
You think I'll sit still
while some un-American foreigner...

779
00:55:36,916 --> 00:55:39,710
...makes accusations about
my own flesh and blood?

780
00:55:39,878 --> 00:55:42,004
We'll see about that. Stop this car!

781
00:55:43,423 --> 00:55:45,841
- Really, madam.
- Mother, this is awful!

782
00:55:46,009 --> 00:55:48,427
- So we'll see!
- Mother, what are you doing?

783
00:55:48,595 --> 00:55:51,430
You don't trust your brother-in-law?
Let me tell you something.

784
00:55:51,598 --> 00:55:54,266
If my boy is out, then everybody is out.
So we'll see.

785
00:55:54,434 --> 00:55:57,436
We don't even own the car
and you have no right to do what you do.

786
00:55:57,604 --> 00:56:02,566
Rights? You talk to me about rights?

787
00:56:02,734 --> 00:56:03,776
Mother...

788
00:56:03,943 --> 00:56:06,653
You address me on the subject of rights?

789
00:56:10,033 --> 00:56:12,117
Trouble? Having any trouble?

790
00:56:12,285 --> 00:56:15,579
Yes! And we don't need
any help from you.

791
00:56:21,628 --> 00:56:23,212
Well!

792
00:56:23,380 --> 00:56:24,838
- Mother, please.
- Ah!

793
00:56:25,006 --> 00:56:26,590
With all due respect, this is too much.

794
00:56:26,758 --> 00:56:29,176
Give Mr. Hawthorne the keys
or we'll never get there.

795
00:56:29,344 --> 00:56:30,260
Too bad.

796
00:56:30,428 --> 00:56:34,390
Madam, I must say I find your attitude
somewhat less than helpful.

797
00:56:34,557 --> 00:56:38,268
And what's all this got to do with you,
if you don't mind telling me?

798
00:56:38,436 --> 00:56:41,980
If we have quite decided
to withdraw from this affair...

799
00:56:42,148 --> 00:56:46,819
...you might be expected to hand me back
my keys so that I could press on.

800
00:56:46,986 --> 00:56:51,198
You keep out of this!
Are we calling Sylvester or not?

801
00:56:52,909 --> 00:56:53,909
No!

802
00:56:54,828 --> 00:56:58,163
We are not. And I'll tell you why.
Because your son, Sylvester...

803
00:56:58,331 --> 00:57:02,501
...is an irresponsible, unreliable,
big loudmouth, no-good bum...

804
00:57:02,669 --> 00:57:04,837
...who, if he isn't a crook,
it's only because...

805
00:57:05,004 --> 00:57:07,965
...he hasn't got the brains or ambition
even to become a crook.

806
00:57:08,133 --> 00:57:09,133
Good show!

807
00:57:09,300 --> 00:57:12,845
If you want to come, you can.
If you don't want to, you don't have to.

808
00:57:13,012 --> 00:57:16,807
But you've got to give us those keys or
you'll force us to take them from you!

809
00:57:16,975 --> 00:57:18,308
Here, here.

810
00:57:24,983 --> 00:57:28,152
Give us those keys.
Give us those keys.

811
00:57:28,319 --> 00:57:30,320
I don't care where you have them.
I'll get them.

812
00:57:30,488 --> 00:57:32,865
- How dare you.
- Give us those keys.

813
00:57:33,032 --> 00:57:36,243
- You take one more step towards me...
- I'll take another step.

814
00:57:36,411 --> 00:57:39,705
I'm warning you.
You're gonna be sorry!

815
00:57:39,873 --> 00:57:42,708
- Give me the keys.
- You're gonna get it, but good!

816
00:57:42,876 --> 00:57:44,793
- Ah!
- Oof!

817
00:57:44,961 --> 00:57:48,046
- Emmeline!
- Emmeline, stay in the car!

818
00:57:49,048 --> 00:57:50,591
Grab her!

819
00:57:53,344 --> 00:57:55,929
Russell, don't! Mother!

820
00:57:56,556 --> 00:57:59,057
- Put me down!
- Must be stuck.

821
00:57:59,225 --> 00:58:02,478
Russell, you wouldn't.
You couldn't! You shouldn't!

822
00:58:02,645 --> 00:58:05,230
Let me go! Let me get out of here!

823
00:58:05,398 --> 00:58:08,650
I got 'em! Here they are.

824
00:58:08,818 --> 00:58:13,322
We really didn't want to do it.
But that was the only way. Upsy-daisy.

825
00:58:14,574 --> 00:58:17,075
Don't hit him. Ow!

826
00:58:20,163 --> 00:58:22,581
Madam, please! Please!

827
00:58:22,749 --> 00:58:24,458
You forced us. You forced us.

828
00:58:24,626 --> 00:58:26,877
I'm willing to say I'm sorry,
but you forced us.

829
00:58:27,045 --> 00:58:30,881
- Do us a favor and get back in the car.
- Get away from me! Don't you touch me!

830
00:58:31,049 --> 00:58:33,926
- We had to do it. You saw it, honey.
- Russell, let me go.

831
00:58:34,093 --> 00:58:36,512
Just wait.
You can't manhandle a decent woman.

832
00:58:36,679 --> 00:58:39,181
You're going to jail!
You'll be arrested for assault.

833
00:58:39,349 --> 00:58:43,101
I'm going to sue for everything you've
got. Take your hands off my daughter!

834
00:58:43,269 --> 00:58:45,687
I say, if we are going,
we really must get cracking.

835
00:58:45,855 --> 00:58:47,022
Russell, how could you?

836
00:58:47,190 --> 00:58:48,899
- You know we had to...
- Mr. Finch!

837
00:58:49,067 --> 00:58:53,111
Please don't go. We'll be right
with you. See, she made us do it.

838
00:58:53,279 --> 00:58:55,405
Let's forget the whole thing
and be reasonable.

839
00:58:55,573 --> 00:58:58,492
- Please get back in the car.
- Not me!

840
00:58:58,660 --> 00:59:01,578
We are wasting so much time.
Give me the keys.

841
00:59:18,429 --> 00:59:20,389
The cars are going faster than we are.

842
00:59:20,557 --> 00:59:22,599
Can't you make this thing
go a little faster?

843
00:59:22,767 --> 00:59:26,812
Wide open, I can.
But wide open eats up a lot of gas.

844
00:59:26,980 --> 00:59:29,648
Then open up wide. I'll pay for the gas.

845
00:59:29,816 --> 00:59:33,402
- It'll cost you about $50.
- Okay, I'll pay when we land.

846
00:59:33,570 --> 00:59:35,696
- Now!
- I got to pay now?

847
00:59:35,863 --> 00:59:38,907
- Now!
- All right, I'll pay you now.

848
00:59:39,075 --> 00:59:40,409
- Melville...
- What?

849
00:59:40,577 --> 00:59:42,536
A bug! Get him off!

850
00:59:42,704 --> 00:59:46,331
Get him off! There he is! Get him!

851
00:59:46,499 --> 00:59:49,543
- You're breaking up the airplane!
- Is it down there?

852
00:59:51,337 --> 00:59:53,297
Now you're breaking the floor!

853
00:59:53,464 --> 00:59:55,173
- Help!
- Melville!

854
00:59:55,341 --> 00:59:58,594
None of these 10 people
have any record at all.

855
00:59:58,761 --> 01:00:01,513
And we're ready to book 'em
for withholding information...

856
01:00:01,681 --> 01:00:04,516
...causing accidents,
failing to report accidents...

857
01:00:04,684 --> 01:00:08,437
...reckless driving, theft, at least
three cases of assault and battery...

858
01:00:08,605 --> 01:00:10,480
- Capt. Culpeper?
- Yeah.

859
01:00:10,648 --> 01:00:12,566
- That my home?
- Yes, sir.

860
01:00:12,734 --> 01:00:15,652
Uh, Sheriff, excuse me. Another call.

861
01:00:15,820 --> 01:00:19,114
Take the Sheriff. I'll take it in here.

862
01:00:19,282 --> 01:00:21,825
Freddy, transfer Mrs. Culpeper
to Culpeper's office.

863
01:00:25,204 --> 01:00:28,415
- Hello, Ginger?
- Daddy, it's Billie Sue.

864
01:00:28,583 --> 01:00:31,543
Oh. Let me speak with
your mother, sweetheart.

865
01:00:34,422 --> 01:00:35,922
Well?

866
01:00:36,716 --> 01:00:38,300
Ah, dear.

867
01:00:38,468 --> 01:00:42,012
Tell me something, Ginger.
How does it feel being married...

868
01:00:42,180 --> 01:00:45,932
...to the most brilliant personality
in the law enforcement industry?

869
01:00:46,100 --> 01:00:48,477
Are you referring to yourself?

870
01:00:48,645 --> 01:00:52,814
Ginger, I want you to prepare yourself
for a little shock.

871
01:00:53,650 --> 01:00:55,067
When I tell you what has happened...

872
01:00:55,234 --> 01:00:58,070
So tell me.
I've got this biscuit dough...

873
01:00:58,237 --> 01:01:01,657
The Smiler Grogan case is solved.

874
01:01:01,824 --> 01:01:03,408
The what?

875
01:01:03,576 --> 01:01:07,829
What the hell is the Smiler Grogan case?

876
01:01:10,458 --> 01:01:12,793
The tuna factory robbery.

877
01:01:12,960 --> 01:01:16,588
The case I've been talking about
for the last 15 years.

878
01:01:17,548 --> 01:01:21,218
All I want you to do
is make all the preparations...

879
01:01:21,386 --> 01:01:24,346
...for a little flight to Hawaii,
Sunday morning.

880
01:01:24,514 --> 01:01:27,265
- So what's the gag?
- It is no gag.

881
01:01:27,433 --> 01:01:30,769
Are you serious
about flying to Hawaii?

882
01:01:32,438 --> 01:01:35,065
Flight 7, Sunday morning.

883
01:01:35,233 --> 01:01:37,776
- Are we taking Billie Sue?
- No!

884
01:01:38,653 --> 01:01:41,029
Just the two of us
for about three weeks.

885
01:01:41,197 --> 01:01:43,407
Now, we're going to celebrate, Ginger.

886
01:01:44,117 --> 01:01:47,077
My feeling is that after 27 years...

887
01:01:48,413 --> 01:01:50,080
...we've earned it.

888
01:02:06,723 --> 01:02:07,723
What's the matter?

889
01:02:07,890 --> 01:02:10,058
- I need help. Can you give me a lift?
- What?

890
01:02:10,226 --> 01:02:13,103
My wife is sick.
The doc sent me out for some medicine.

891
01:02:13,271 --> 01:02:14,187
All right. Come on.

892
01:02:14,355 --> 01:02:16,314
- I just ran out of gas.
- Get in!

893
01:02:31,664 --> 01:02:32,789
- You?
- You?

894
01:02:32,957 --> 01:02:34,499
Wait a minute. We're in trouble.

895
01:02:34,667 --> 01:02:37,002
Everybody's in trouble.
Get out of the way.

896
01:02:37,170 --> 01:02:39,504
You think we wanted
to leave you back there?

897
01:02:39,672 --> 01:02:41,006
It was my son-in-law
and that Englishman.

898
01:02:41,174 --> 01:02:43,508
What Englishman? Get out of the way.

899
01:02:43,676 --> 01:02:47,387
You leave us here,
and you know what you're going to get?

900
01:02:47,555 --> 01:02:49,639
Nothing! We'll get it all.

901
01:02:49,807 --> 01:02:50,766
How will you do that?

902
01:02:50,933 --> 01:02:53,810
I'll call my son. He lives
about 10 miles from Rosita Beach.

903
01:02:53,978 --> 01:02:58,190
He'll drive there and get the money
and we're going to have it. That's how!

904
01:02:58,357 --> 01:03:01,651
I was going to offer you a share
for taking us to a phone.

905
01:03:01,819 --> 01:03:05,447
But because you're not interested,
we'll wait for another car.

906
01:03:05,615 --> 01:03:07,240
We're making a terrible mistake.

907
01:03:07,408 --> 01:03:09,284
We should go back
and get my mother-in-law.

908
01:03:09,452 --> 01:03:10,744
- Go back?
- Yes.

909
01:03:10,912 --> 01:03:12,078
You couldn't be serious.

910
01:03:12,246 --> 01:03:16,124
All she has to do is get to a telephone,
my brother-in-law will get there first.

911
01:03:16,292 --> 01:03:20,378
They'll get all and we won't get a dime.
You can believe that.

912
01:03:23,508 --> 01:03:25,217
But look here.

913
01:03:25,384 --> 01:03:28,595
Even if she does get all the money,
this won't make any difference...

914
01:03:28,763 --> 01:03:31,765
...to our agreement.
She wouldn't break her word.

915
01:03:31,933 --> 01:03:36,645
I mean to say, I'd still be entitled
to 10 percent as agreed. Surely.

916
01:03:37,438 --> 01:03:40,357
Surely. Come on, let's go.

917
01:04:03,089 --> 01:04:06,508
- Operator.
- Santa Rosita 7-1-9-6-5.

918
01:04:06,676 --> 01:04:10,595
...and then that dirty, rotten,
slimy bum that double-crossed me.

919
01:04:10,763 --> 01:04:13,849
When I get a hold of that smart aleck,
what I'm going to do...

920
01:04:14,016 --> 01:04:16,768
If you're there, I hope you turn away...

921
01:04:16,936 --> 01:04:19,604
...that's all,
that you just look the other way.

922
01:04:23,109 --> 01:04:24,109
Did you get him?

923
01:04:24,277 --> 01:04:26,611
Maybe he went out
for the papers or something.

924
01:04:26,779 --> 01:04:28,738
We can keep on trying.

925
01:04:28,906 --> 01:04:33,243
Just supposing we never do get him?
We might be the last ones there.

926
01:04:47,133 --> 01:04:50,135
Just a minute. Down there?

927
01:04:50,303 --> 01:04:51,887
You're kidding. It's too steep.

928
01:04:52,054 --> 01:04:54,723
I drive my jeep down here every day.
Let's go!

929
01:04:54,891 --> 01:04:56,182
Yeah, let's go. Let's...

930
01:05:14,243 --> 01:05:17,579
You can turn around here.
I sure appreciate this, mister. Thanks.

931
01:05:17,747 --> 01:05:19,998
Yeah, swell, yeah.

932
01:05:23,419 --> 01:05:24,753
Hi, Eddie.

933
01:06:19,266 --> 01:06:20,684
I got to get out of here.

934
01:06:20,851 --> 01:06:24,229
Will you ask your father to show me?
There must be some other way out!

935
01:06:24,397 --> 01:06:26,314
Come on! Hurry up!

936
01:06:31,821 --> 01:06:35,657
I could show you a way out.
There's another way to the road.

937
01:06:35,825 --> 01:06:39,953
You know another way to the road?
Good. Come on in. Don't stand there.

938
01:06:40,121 --> 01:06:43,289
If you show me the way out,
I'll give you $1.

939
01:06:43,457 --> 01:06:45,583
- Hm... $3.
- $3? Why, you...

940
01:06:45,751 --> 01:06:47,669
Yeah, all right. I'll give you $3.

941
01:06:47,837 --> 01:06:52,382
But don't stand there, hop in the car.
Hurry kid, I got to get out of here!

942
01:07:06,230 --> 01:07:08,273
- They're not here.
- Probably got a lift.

943
01:07:08,441 --> 01:07:11,192
We only passed six or seven cars
and they weren't in them.

944
01:07:11,360 --> 01:07:13,236
Somebody must have
taken them the other way.

945
01:07:13,404 --> 01:07:15,905
I think we better go back
to that place we phoned from.

946
01:07:16,073 --> 01:07:18,116
What? That's miles
in the wrong direction.

947
01:07:18,284 --> 01:07:20,285
Besides, we can't be certain
they'll be there.

948
01:07:20,453 --> 01:07:23,538
I don't know, I must find my wife.
And I don't know what to do.

949
01:07:23,706 --> 01:07:25,123
Wherever they are...

950
01:07:25,291 --> 01:07:28,626
...surely the most sensible thing
is for the two of us to press on.

951
01:07:28,794 --> 01:07:31,921
For all we know, your brother-in-law
may be out or away somewhere.

952
01:07:32,089 --> 01:07:35,884
Even if he were the first there,
he still has to find the money.

953
01:07:36,052 --> 01:07:38,887
I earnestly recommend
we forget your good ladies...

954
01:07:39,055 --> 01:07:40,930
...and press on
with all possible dispatch.

955
01:07:41,098 --> 01:07:43,808
All right. We'll press on
with all possible dispatch.

956
01:07:43,976 --> 01:07:46,644
And I don't really think
that personal rancor...

957
01:07:46,812 --> 01:07:50,231
...is going to help the situation,
if I may say so.

958
01:08:06,457 --> 01:08:09,876
Okay, come on, honey.
Let's go. We're here.

959
01:08:10,044 --> 01:08:14,506
We got here first. Let's go.
Come on. I got you.

960
01:08:14,673 --> 01:08:15,840
Atta boy, baby.

961
01:08:16,008 --> 01:08:18,009
We made it. We're here first.

962
01:08:18,177 --> 01:08:20,303
Take care of my car
until we get back, right?

963
01:08:20,471 --> 01:08:24,599
Come on, let's go.
Will you go? Come on!

964
01:08:31,023 --> 01:08:32,440
Over there?

965
01:08:33,109 --> 01:08:34,359
There?

966
01:08:35,152 --> 01:08:36,694
Down there?

967
01:09:09,478 --> 01:09:11,104
That'll be $2.90.

968
01:09:11,272 --> 01:09:15,233
$2.90? Here's $3.00.
Keep the change, but wait for us, okay?

969
01:09:15,401 --> 01:09:16,734
Oh, sure.

970
01:09:17,278 --> 01:09:19,737
Wise guy. Come on, let's go.

971
01:09:20,531 --> 01:09:23,366
- No, we're closed. It's 12:00.
- It's 12:00. They're closed.

972
01:09:23,534 --> 01:09:27,787
Wait a minute!
All we want is a pick and a shovel!

973
01:09:27,955 --> 01:09:29,414
Mr. Dinkler's inside.

974
01:09:29,582 --> 01:09:32,500
Dinkler. That's it.
We'll get Dinkler. Come on.

975
01:09:34,336 --> 01:09:35,420
Ah!

976
01:09:35,588 --> 01:09:37,046
Downstairs. Come on.

977
01:09:37,214 --> 01:09:39,883
They must be here someplace.
Down here, yeah.

978
01:09:42,094 --> 01:09:43,970
Look for a pick and a shovel, all right?

979
01:09:44,138 --> 01:09:46,973
Pick and a shovel,
must be someplace around.

980
01:09:47,141 --> 01:09:48,766
That's all I need.

981
01:09:48,934 --> 01:09:52,478
That's all I need, boy.
That's all I need, a pick and a shovel.

982
01:09:52,646 --> 01:09:53,730
I found it!

983
01:10:00,696 --> 01:10:02,405
Got it!

984
01:10:02,573 --> 01:10:04,407
- But there...
- I got it! I found it!

985
01:10:08,871 --> 01:10:12,207
I've no wish to quarrel with you,
but speaking as a representative...

986
01:10:12,374 --> 01:10:15,752
...of Her Majesty's Armed Forces,
I take the most particular exception...

987
01:10:15,920 --> 01:10:18,630
You want me to tell you something?
As far as I'm concerned...

988
01:10:18,797 --> 01:10:20,965
...the whole British race
is practically finished.

989
01:10:21,133 --> 01:10:24,010
If we hadn't kept
your whole country afloat...

990
01:10:24,178 --> 01:10:27,138
...by giving you billions
you never even said thank you for...

991
01:10:27,306 --> 01:10:31,226
...the whole phony outfit would be
sunk under the Atlantic years ago.

992
01:10:31,393 --> 01:10:32,810
Hey.

993
01:10:32,978 --> 01:10:35,813
- What are you stopping for?
- Get out of this machine.

994
01:10:35,981 --> 01:10:37,565
Get out? You're crazy!

995
01:10:37,733 --> 01:10:40,151
It's my machine.
I'll do as I bloody well please. Out!

996
01:10:40,319 --> 01:10:43,613
I'm awfully sorry.
I've been very edgy today.

997
01:10:43,781 --> 01:10:46,991
If I said anything about England,
I apologize.

998
01:10:47,159 --> 01:10:49,035
I'm glad to hear you say so.

999
01:10:49,203 --> 01:10:51,079
I must say, if I had the misfortune

1000
01:10:51,247 --> 01:10:53,331
to be a citizen
of this benighted country...

1001
01:10:53,499 --> 01:10:57,502
...I should be most hesitant
in offering any criticism of any other.

1002
01:10:57,670 --> 01:10:59,545
Wait a minute.
Are you knocking this country?

1003
01:10:59,713 --> 01:11:01,839
Are you saying something
against America?

1004
01:11:02,007 --> 01:11:02,924
Against it?

1005
01:11:03,092 --> 01:11:06,427
I'd be astounded to hear
anything said for it.

1006
01:11:06,595 --> 01:11:09,389
The whole bloody place
is the most unspeakable matriarchy...

1007
01:11:09,556 --> 01:11:11,015
...in the history of civilization.

1008
01:11:11,183 --> 01:11:15,019
Look at yourself, the way your wife
and her strumpet of a mother...

1009
01:11:15,187 --> 01:11:16,604
...push you through the hoop.

1010
01:11:16,772 --> 01:11:19,691
As far as I can see, American men
have been totally emasculated.

1011
01:11:19,858 --> 01:11:20,942
They're like slaves.

1012
01:11:21,110 --> 01:11:23,319
They die like flies
from coronary thrombosis...

1013
01:11:23,487 --> 01:11:26,447
...while their women sit under
hair dryers eating chocolates...

1014
01:11:26,615 --> 01:11:30,827
...and arranging for every second
Tuesday to be some sort of Mother's Day.

1015
01:11:30,995 --> 01:11:34,831
And this positively infantile
preoccupation with bosoms.

1016
01:11:34,999 --> 01:11:37,000
In all my time
in this wretched country...

1017
01:11:37,167 --> 01:11:41,546
...the one thing that has appalled me
most is this preoccupation with bosoms.

1018
01:11:41,714 --> 01:11:44,924
They've become the dominant theme
in American culture:

1019
01:11:45,092 --> 01:11:48,219
In literature, in advertising,
in entertainment, in everything.

1020
01:11:48,387 --> 01:11:50,138
I'll wager you anything you like...

1021
01:11:50,306 --> 01:11:52,724
...if American women
stopped wearing brassieres...

1022
01:11:52,891 --> 01:11:56,477
...your whole national economy
would collapse overnight.

1023
01:11:57,855 --> 01:11:59,814
F-7 to Central.
The Crumps are locked...

1024
01:11:59,982 --> 01:12:02,900
...in the hardware store basement.
Shall I let them out? Over.

1025
01:12:03,068 --> 01:12:05,653
How could they get locked in a basement?

1026
01:12:05,821 --> 01:12:08,823
- We better let them out.
- That ain't fair.

1027
01:12:08,991 --> 01:12:12,618
- It ain't fair? What ain't fair?
- They got themselves in there.

1028
01:12:12,786 --> 01:12:14,579
They ought to be able
to get themselves out.

1029
01:12:14,747 --> 01:12:19,292
Uh, after all, if you help them,
you're not being fair to the others.

1030
01:12:19,460 --> 01:12:22,253
But the moment anybody
gets to where they're going...

1031
01:12:22,421 --> 01:12:23,421
...we'll pick them up.

1032
01:12:23,589 --> 01:12:25,757
What difference does it make
who gets there first?

1033
01:12:25,924 --> 01:12:27,216
It's a race, ain't it?

1034
01:12:27,384 --> 01:12:28,968
Why do you want to help that dentist?

1035
01:12:29,136 --> 01:12:33,348
Me? I've been pulling for that guy Pike
with the furniture van.

1036
01:12:33,515 --> 01:12:35,433
The rules should be the same
for everybody.

1037
01:12:35,601 --> 01:12:37,435
Otherwise, it just ain't fair.

1038
01:12:45,778 --> 01:12:47,528
Central to F-7.

1039
01:12:48,405 --> 01:12:51,783
No. We'll leave them where they are.
See what happens.

1040
01:12:51,950 --> 01:12:55,453
Watch all the exits,
but render no assistance. Over.

1041
01:12:59,291 --> 01:13:00,708
Are you happy?

1042
01:13:24,024 --> 01:13:25,233
I need a drink.

1043
01:13:25,401 --> 01:13:28,736
There's some ice and stuff back there.
Make us all some Old Fashioneds.

1044
01:13:28,904 --> 01:13:31,072
You think you ought to drink
while you're flying?

1045
01:13:31,240 --> 01:13:33,241
Stop kidding and make us some drinks.

1046
01:13:33,409 --> 01:13:36,494
Just press the button back there
marked "booze. "

1047
01:13:37,621 --> 01:13:40,289
It's the only way to fly.

1048
01:13:54,847 --> 01:13:57,974
Estimated speed 175.

1049
01:13:58,142 --> 01:14:00,184
We'll never be able to keep up with him.

1050
01:14:00,352 --> 01:14:03,604
Better have some of the other units
intercept. Over.

1051
01:14:05,190 --> 01:14:07,316
Hello, Ginger?
What's the matter now?

1052
01:14:07,484 --> 01:14:10,736
It's Billie Sue.
Her new boyfriend Oscar...

1053
01:14:10,904 --> 01:14:14,240
...was supposed to come down
from Pomona just to meet us.

1054
01:14:14,408 --> 01:14:17,076
So now she told him
we were going away.

1055
01:14:17,244 --> 01:14:18,661
What? What's the matter?

1056
01:14:18,829 --> 01:14:22,415
You keep forgetting.
If a girl is 6 feet 5 inches tall...

1057
01:14:22,583 --> 01:14:24,709
...she's bound to have special problems.

1058
01:14:24,877 --> 01:14:26,752
- But, Ginger...
- They had some argument...

1059
01:14:26,920 --> 01:14:27,837
Get out!

1060
01:14:28,005 --> 01:14:30,798
...screaming at each other.
Now the whole engagement's off...

1061
01:14:30,966 --> 01:14:32,758
...and she says she's leaving.

1062
01:14:32,926 --> 01:14:35,344
Leaving what? Leaving home?

1063
01:14:35,512 --> 01:14:37,513
Let me talk to her.
Get her to the phone.

1064
01:14:37,681 --> 01:14:40,266
I'll try. Just a minute.
Talk to your father.

1065
01:14:40,434 --> 01:14:43,186
I won't.
I don't want to talk to him ever.

1066
01:14:43,353 --> 01:14:47,231
Don't be ridiculous.
Whatever else he is, he is your father.

1067
01:15:10,589 --> 01:15:14,008
Ah!

1068
01:15:15,135 --> 01:15:16,427
Ah!

1069
01:15:39,451 --> 01:15:43,120
Ooh! Yeah! Ah!

1070
01:15:46,083 --> 01:15:48,709
Oh!

1071
01:15:51,463 --> 01:15:53,506
You hear bells, baby?

1072
01:15:58,178 --> 01:15:59,095
Yes?

1073
01:15:59,263 --> 01:16:02,265
- Who is that?
- Who's that?

1074
01:16:02,432 --> 01:16:04,058
I want my son! Hey!

1075
01:16:06,562 --> 01:16:10,314
Who is that?
I want to speak to Sylvester Marcus.

1076
01:16:10,482 --> 01:16:13,401
- Sylvester?
- Yeah, baby?

1077
01:16:13,569 --> 01:16:16,529
It's your mom.

1078
01:16:16,697 --> 01:16:21,158
Ah! Good old Mom. Hello!

1079
01:16:21,326 --> 01:16:23,786
- Sylvester?
- Is that you, Mom?

1080
01:16:23,954 --> 01:16:26,581
Of course it's me.
I've been trying you all morning.

1081
01:16:26,748 --> 01:16:29,333
I've been a little busy.

1082
01:16:29,501 --> 01:16:32,169
I've been working
and I didn't hear the phone.

1083
01:16:32,337 --> 01:16:34,297
Hold on a minute, will you, Mom?

1084
01:16:34,464 --> 01:16:38,092
Baby, how about a beer or something?
Man, I feel like...

1085
01:16:38,260 --> 01:16:40,469
Will you listen?
Something's happened.

1086
01:16:40,637 --> 01:16:43,931
There was an accident this
morning. A man got killed!

1087
01:16:44,099 --> 01:16:45,182
Who got killed?

1088
01:16:45,350 --> 01:16:47,018
- Now, listen!
- You all right?

1089
01:16:47,185 --> 01:16:48,644
- Pay attention!
- Sis all right?

1090
01:16:48,812 --> 01:16:50,438
- Will you listen?
- What's wrong?

1091
01:16:50,606 --> 01:16:52,023
Can you hear me?

1092
01:16:52,190 --> 01:16:53,941
There's a whole fortune in cash.

1093
01:16:54,109 --> 01:16:57,445
You can get it before anybody else,
but you've got to hurry!

1094
01:16:57,613 --> 01:17:00,698
What's the matter? What's going on
there? Are you all right?

1095
01:17:00,866 --> 01:17:03,534
Of course I'm all right. Sylvester!

1096
01:17:03,702 --> 01:17:04,952
Are Russell and Emmeline with you?

1097
01:17:05,120 --> 01:17:09,123
Forget about Russell.
Will you shut up and let me talk?

1098
01:17:09,291 --> 01:17:11,667
What's going on? Where's Russell?

1099
01:17:11,835 --> 01:17:13,836
Don't even mention Russell!

1100
01:17:14,004 --> 01:17:17,340
- When I tell you what Russell did...
- Just tell him about the dough.

1101
01:17:17,507 --> 01:17:18,841
Keep out of this! Shut up!

1102
01:17:19,009 --> 01:17:21,552
- Don't talk. Just listen.
- What did Russell do?

1103
01:17:21,720 --> 01:17:25,348
He assaulted me, if you wanna know!
He grabbed me beside the road.

1104
01:17:25,515 --> 01:17:27,892
He and this Englishman
I don't even know!

1105
01:17:28,060 --> 01:17:30,394
Who's with you and where are you?

1106
01:17:30,562 --> 01:17:34,523
I'm with this truck driver
in Peterson's Garage in Plaster City.

1107
01:17:34,691 --> 01:17:37,026
Will you shut up a minute
so I can tell you what happened?

1108
01:17:37,194 --> 01:17:41,697
Listen to me close! Stay there,
'cause I'm coming to get you right now.

1109
01:17:41,865 --> 01:17:42,823
Shut up and listen!

1110
01:17:42,991 --> 01:17:46,702
Everything's going to be all right.
Your baby's coming to get you.

1111
01:17:46,870 --> 01:17:49,080
- Sit there. Relax. Take it easy.
- Sylvester!

1112
01:17:49,247 --> 01:17:52,166
I'm coming.
Everything's going to be all right.

1113
01:17:56,213 --> 01:17:57,421
Well?

1114
01:17:58,256 --> 01:18:02,468
So he's coming here,
and I'm not to worry about a thing.

1115
01:18:02,636 --> 01:18:05,680
Because everything
is going to be all right.

1116
01:18:06,431 --> 01:18:10,559
Exactly like your father:
A big, stupid, muscle-headed moron!

1117
01:18:11,645 --> 01:18:13,521
The burglar alarm.

1118
01:18:13,689 --> 01:18:17,525
We just throw it on, people hear it,
they come, and we're out.

1119
01:18:17,693 --> 01:18:20,069
Don't be frightened
if it makes a big bell noise.

1120
01:18:20,237 --> 01:18:22,446
Okay? All right? Here we go.

1121
01:18:26,868 --> 01:18:30,788
- I don't hear anything.
- Neither do I. There's no bell.

1122
01:18:35,085 --> 01:18:37,503
Look at it. It just stands there.

1123
01:18:38,630 --> 01:18:39,964
Wait a minute.

1124
01:18:42,134 --> 01:18:43,676
Stand back.

1125
01:18:58,316 --> 01:19:00,860
Burglar alarm!

1126
01:19:01,027 --> 01:19:03,154
The stupidest burglar in the world
could come in...

1127
01:19:03,321 --> 01:19:06,073
...and walk away with everything,
and we can't even get out.

1128
01:19:06,241 --> 01:19:08,993
Sheesh!

1129
01:19:09,161 --> 01:19:10,995
Come here!

1130
01:19:18,795 --> 01:19:21,672
Melville? Melville!

1131
01:19:21,840 --> 01:19:25,676
Even if you do get the bell to ring
and somebody comes...

1132
01:19:25,844 --> 01:19:27,762
...what about the damage?

1133
01:19:29,556 --> 01:19:32,183
They're the ones who locked us in!

1134
01:19:33,769 --> 01:19:36,353
This thing has got to work.

1135
01:19:42,027 --> 01:19:43,027
No!

1136
01:19:43,987 --> 01:19:47,865
Please, help me! I'm frying!
Ah! Please! Help me!

1137
01:20:01,087 --> 01:20:03,547
Uh... Don't make them
so sweet this time.

1138
01:20:03,715 --> 01:20:06,759
You've had two already.
Can't you wait till we're on the ground?

1139
01:20:06,927 --> 01:20:09,512
What are you talking about?
I'll make the next batch.

1140
01:20:09,679 --> 01:20:11,055
You take the controls.

1141
01:20:11,223 --> 01:20:14,809
- I don't know how to fly an airplane.
- There's really nothing to it.

1142
01:20:14,976 --> 01:20:19,271
- But Benjy can't fly!
- Nonsense. Anybody can fly a plane.

1143
01:20:19,439 --> 01:20:22,733
I'll check you out.
Put your little hands on the wheel.

1144
01:20:22,901 --> 01:20:25,611
That's it. Now you have it.
Now the feet on the rudder.

1145
01:20:25,779 --> 01:20:27,696
There you are, feet on the rudder.

1146
01:20:27,864 --> 01:20:31,075
Who says this boy can't fly a plane?
There you go.

1147
01:20:31,243 --> 01:20:33,702
I'm making an Old Fashioned
the old-fashioned way...

1148
01:20:33,870 --> 01:20:35,913
...the way dear old Dad used to.

1149
01:20:36,081 --> 01:20:37,623
What if something happens?

1150
01:20:37,791 --> 01:20:40,876
What can happen
to an Old Fashioned, all right?

1151
01:20:43,046 --> 01:20:46,298
I know you don't know what to do,
so don't do nothing.

1152
01:20:46,466 --> 01:20:50,594
- I won't do nothing.
- That boy's a natural-born flyer.

1153
01:21:01,231 --> 01:21:04,608
Wait a minute. Benjy! Benjy!
Ease back on her!

1154
01:21:04,776 --> 01:21:06,569
- I'm easing.
- Ease back a little!

1155
01:21:06,736 --> 01:21:10,155
- I'm trying my best.
- All kidding aside...

1156
01:21:10,323 --> 01:21:13,075
I'm not kidding any longer.
It's making me...

1157
01:21:13,243 --> 01:21:16,704
...nervous!
Hey! We've got an accident back here!

1158
01:21:16,872 --> 01:21:18,455
- What happened?
- I don't know!

1159
01:21:24,880 --> 01:21:26,088
Oh!

1160
01:21:26,256 --> 01:21:28,841
It's good that truck pulled over.
I can't stand this anymore.

1161
01:21:29,009 --> 01:21:31,051
In the name of reason,
pull yourself together.

1162
01:21:31,219 --> 01:21:32,720
You were 10 feet over the line.

1163
01:22:11,176 --> 01:22:12,551
Uh!

1164
01:22:12,719 --> 01:22:16,055
Oh! So it's fisticuffs you want, is it?
Right. Stick them up!

1165
01:22:16,222 --> 01:22:18,349
- No! No!
- Come here, you coward!

1166
01:22:18,516 --> 01:22:20,392
No! Don't hit me!

1167
01:22:20,560 --> 01:22:22,436
- Stop, you!
- Don't hit me!

1168
01:22:26,691 --> 01:22:29,902
- Blood.
- It certainly is.

1169
01:22:31,738 --> 01:22:33,822
Come back here, you blimey...

1170
01:22:38,370 --> 01:22:41,080
You want to play dirty, huh? Okay!

1171
01:22:44,918 --> 01:22:46,043
Foul! Foul!

1172
01:22:46,211 --> 01:22:47,169
You're not much good...

1173
01:22:47,337 --> 01:22:49,630
...without that horrible
mother-in-law of yours, are you?

1174
01:22:49,798 --> 01:22:52,216
Ow!

1175
01:22:53,635 --> 01:22:55,386
Come on. Fight!

1176
01:22:55,553 --> 01:22:57,805
You thought you had me, didn't you?

1177
01:22:57,973 --> 01:22:59,515
I'll kill you. I swear!

1178
01:22:59,683 --> 01:23:04,228
No, stop, please! No, please.

1179
01:23:17,492 --> 01:23:20,119
- Hello. Hello there.
- Don't shut the motor off!

1180
01:23:20,286 --> 01:23:23,622
I'm not shutting anything off!
Hello, anybody! Can anybody hear me?

1181
01:23:23,790 --> 01:23:27,543
- I can hear you!
- I don't care if you hear me!

1182
01:23:27,711 --> 01:23:28,585
Look, I wanna be...

1183
01:23:28,753 --> 01:23:31,839
- I don't know whether we're on the air.
