- That's out of my way.

1414
01:39:00,351 --> 01:39:01,726
- We're blocking traffic.
- We are?

1415
01:39:01,894 --> 01:39:03,019
Let's move it. Move it.

1416
01:39:18,035 --> 01:39:19,619
There we go. All right.

1417
01:39:20,454 --> 01:39:22,872
You hide behind the counter.
I'll light up a fuse.

1418
01:39:23,040 --> 01:39:27,251
Melville, will you just do one thing
for me before you use the dynamite?

1419
01:39:27,419 --> 01:39:30,129
Try hitting the door just once more.

1420
01:39:30,297 --> 01:39:34,384
Honey, I broke my back on that door.
That's a hard door. I mean...

1421
01:39:37,888 --> 01:39:39,639
Okay.

1422
01:39:39,807 --> 01:39:41,891
Where's the sledgehammer?

1423
01:39:48,774 --> 01:39:53,277
This staircase isn't safe anymore.
The fire burned it all out.

1424
01:39:53,445 --> 01:39:54,654
Please?

1425
01:39:57,032 --> 01:39:58,366
All right.

1426
01:40:09,461 --> 01:40:11,337
You're going to...

1427
01:40:20,931 --> 01:40:22,515
Melville, for God...

1428
01:40:22,683 --> 01:40:23,933
Melville!

1429
01:40:26,979 --> 01:40:28,354
Monica...

1430
01:40:28,522 --> 01:40:31,482
...now let's forget about the door, huh?

1431
01:40:35,696 --> 01:40:36,654
Look out!

1432
01:40:36,822 --> 01:40:38,823
- What?
- They've spotted us.

1433
01:40:38,991 --> 01:40:41,034
- Who have?
- Don't stop. Keep going.

1434
01:40:41,201 --> 01:40:43,244
- What is this?
- Helicopter. They've seen us.

1435
01:40:43,412 --> 01:40:44,787
What helicopter?

1436
01:40:47,041 --> 01:40:50,460
- That's a police helicopter.
- They always use them.

1437
01:40:50,627 --> 01:40:53,379
- Who?
- Who do you think? Look...

1438
01:40:53,547 --> 01:40:56,299
I don't want to talk about this,
but they got me hemmed in.

1439
01:40:56,467 --> 01:40:58,301
- Who?
- Will you shut up and listen?

1440
01:40:58,469 --> 01:41:02,388
I'm going to break a rule that says
we must never reveal our true identity.

1441
01:41:02,556 --> 01:41:05,308
This is a matter of life or death,
a desperate situation.

1442
01:41:05,476 --> 01:41:07,894
- What is?
- Will you shut up and listen?

1443
01:41:08,062 --> 01:41:10,897
Look, I haven't got much time,
so if you love your country...

1444
01:41:11,065 --> 01:41:13,649
...if you're a patriot, you'll listen,
and listen hard.

1445
01:41:13,817 --> 01:41:15,651
You gotta get to a phone
and make a call.

1446
01:41:15,819 --> 01:41:17,779
- I don't got...
- You got to call Intelligence.

1447
01:41:17,946 --> 01:41:19,947
Central Intelligence Agency
in Washington, D.C.

1448
01:41:20,115 --> 01:41:22,200
- What on earth...
- Now, listen!

1449
01:41:22,367 --> 01:41:25,578
You tell 'em you heard from X-27.
You got it? X-27.

1450
01:41:25,746 --> 01:41:29,207
X-27 told you to tell them they've made
three attempts on my life today.

1451
01:41:29,374 --> 01:41:31,042
They tried to drown me.

1452
01:41:31,210 --> 01:41:33,377
Can you handle a gun? Now, look... Oh!

1453
01:41:33,545 --> 01:41:36,214
There's a cafe. Pull right in there.
You'll use that phone.

1454
01:41:36,381 --> 01:41:38,633
- I don't think I...
- Shut up! You're in no danger.

1455
01:41:38,801 --> 01:41:40,551
They've never seen ya. Now, pull in.

1456
01:41:47,851 --> 01:41:49,685
All right, good. Get to a phone.

1457
01:41:49,853 --> 01:41:53,189
Tell the operator "emergency priority,"
then ask for the CIA.

1458
01:41:53,357 --> 01:41:55,358
Jump out. Come on, come on.

1459
01:41:55,526 --> 01:41:57,401
You're in no danger.
They don't know you.

1460
01:41:57,569 --> 01:42:00,363
You're all right.
I'll duck the car and come back.

1461
01:42:00,531 --> 01:42:02,448
For God's sake,
don't stand in the street.

1462
01:42:02,616 --> 01:42:04,200
They'll see you. They'll spot you!

1463
01:42:04,368 --> 01:42:06,702
Move it. Yah! Go!

1464
01:42:20,217 --> 01:42:23,719
And... Sylvester! It's Sylvester!
Turn around, you idiot!

1465
01:42:23,887 --> 01:42:26,514
What do you want to stop him for?
He's going the wrong way.

1466
01:42:26,682 --> 01:42:29,308
It's my son. Do as you're told, stupid.

1467
01:42:45,993 --> 01:42:46,909
They're nuts.

1468
01:42:47,077 --> 01:42:50,413
Tell them the tow truck turned around
and is following the Dodge.

1469
01:42:51,039 --> 01:42:53,249
2-1-7-1, 2-1-5-9.

1470
01:42:54,585 --> 01:42:56,252
This is stupid.

1471
01:42:56,420 --> 01:42:57,920
You call me a stupid idiot.

1472
01:42:58,088 --> 01:43:00,381
Let me tell you something.
You're a stupid idiot.

1473
01:43:00,549 --> 01:43:04,468
- He'll go all the way to Plaster City.
- So he goes to Plaster City.

1474
01:43:04,636 --> 01:43:07,263
I don't know about you,
but I'm turning this thing around.

1475
01:43:07,431 --> 01:43:10,641
Now, you want to catch him,
you get out and run.

1476
01:43:30,913 --> 01:43:32,580
Let's stop arguing. Please.

1477
01:43:32,748 --> 01:43:35,458
The reason we're together
is because they only had one car.

1478
01:43:35,626 --> 01:43:38,461
Let's get there, even if we are last.

1479
01:43:38,629 --> 01:43:42,924
Whatever the outcome of the day,
I shall never forget that you hit me...

1480
01:43:43,091 --> 01:43:45,218
...when I wasn't even looking.

1481
01:43:45,385 --> 01:43:46,385
Yeah.

1482
01:43:55,062 --> 01:43:56,687
Russell!

1483
01:44:09,493 --> 01:44:13,955
- How can you be so slow?
- I've had just about enough out of you.

1484
01:44:14,122 --> 01:44:15,873
If ya turned quicker
we coulda caught him!

1485
01:44:16,041 --> 01:44:19,085
- Why don't you shut up?
- Russell! There!

1486
01:44:19,253 --> 01:44:21,170
It's Russell and Mr. Hawthorne!

1487
01:44:21,338 --> 01:44:22,505
Stop them! Catch them!

1488
01:44:22,673 --> 01:44:24,006
We gonna start that again?

1489
01:44:24,174 --> 01:44:26,717
Faster! Step on it!
Blow the horn, you big dope!

1490
01:44:26,885 --> 01:44:28,552
What do you want them for anyway?

1491
01:44:28,720 --> 01:44:30,721
Keep up with them.
You're falling behind.

1492
01:44:30,889 --> 01:44:33,391
Sylvester! Mother! Sylvester!

1493
01:44:33,558 --> 01:44:36,185
Stop him! Don't let him get away!

1494
01:44:41,275 --> 01:44:44,151
I say, what's that chap
honking his hooter for?

1495
01:44:44,319 --> 01:44:47,154
It's probably some road hog
who thinks he owns...

1496
01:44:47,322 --> 01:44:48,614
- What?
- What?

1497
01:44:48,782 --> 01:44:51,701
I got to ask you something about Mama!
Russell, wait a minute!

1498
01:44:51,868 --> 01:44:54,704
- It's my brother-in-law.
- What's he doing?

1499
01:44:54,871 --> 01:44:57,498
Be careful of him. He's not normal.

1500
01:44:58,500 --> 01:45:01,085
You're getting me...
Boy, are you bugging me, man!

1501
01:45:01,253 --> 01:45:05,214
I'm going to nail...
I'm getting bugged now!

1502
01:45:05,382 --> 01:45:06,340
Whoa, man.

1503
01:45:07,718 --> 01:45:10,052
Russell, if you don't pull over,
I'll kill you!

1504
01:45:10,220 --> 01:45:12,221
I'm warning you,
pull over and stop.

1505
01:45:12,389 --> 01:45:13,764
I said stop!

1506
01:45:13,932 --> 01:45:15,558
You asked for it.

1507
01:45:23,400 --> 01:45:25,151
Russell,
when I get my hands on you...

1508
01:45:26,194 --> 01:45:27,903
What are you doing?

1509
01:45:28,071 --> 01:45:29,572
- I said stop!
- Are you crazy?

1510
01:45:29,740 --> 01:45:31,907
- We'll get killed!
- Pull over!

1511
01:45:42,294 --> 01:45:45,755
Don't you know what I mean?
I said stop that car!

1512
01:45:51,136 --> 01:45:54,430
When I get my hands on you, Russell,
I will kill you!

1513
01:46:13,283 --> 01:46:14,950
Are you crazy?

1514
01:46:15,118 --> 01:46:17,161
Ah!

1515
01:46:23,460 --> 01:46:26,462
I've never seen anything
like this bunch.

1516
01:46:26,630 --> 01:46:29,298
He ran right into them,
ran them right off the road.

1517
01:46:30,467 --> 01:46:34,136
- You guys, come on out of there!
- Fellow's absolutely beside himself.

1518
01:46:34,304 --> 01:46:36,722
- What are you trying to do?
- Let's go!

1519
01:46:36,890 --> 01:46:39,350
- What did you do to my mother?
- We wouldn't do any...

1520
01:46:40,394 --> 01:46:41,477
Move! Move!

1521
01:46:41,645 --> 01:46:45,147
- What did you do to my mother?
- I didn't do anything! Let me explain.

1522
01:46:45,315 --> 01:46:46,649
Look here.

1523
01:46:47,484 --> 01:46:48,984
She called me. She phoned me.

1524
01:46:49,152 --> 01:46:51,821
What she told me was so horrible,
I thought she'd gone nuts!

1525
01:46:51,988 --> 01:46:53,489
- It was true, wasn't it?
- It's not true.

1526
01:46:53,657 --> 01:46:56,450
Whoever told you was a liar.
It's not true.

1527
01:46:56,618 --> 01:46:59,370
- It is true!
- Now, look here!

1528
01:47:00,914 --> 01:47:03,040
Are you English? Just answer me!

1529
01:47:03,208 --> 01:47:06,502
Yes. As a matter of fact, I am.
Don't you like the English?

1530
01:47:09,965 --> 01:47:11,257
There was an Englishman.

1531
01:47:11,425 --> 01:47:14,468
She said that you and this Englishman...
I'll kill you!

1532
01:47:15,846 --> 01:47:17,513
What did you do to my Mama?

1533
01:47:17,681 --> 01:47:20,641
- Emmeline!
- Mama!

1534
01:47:20,809 --> 01:47:23,602
Why couldn't you listen?
Why couldn't you shut up...

1535
01:47:23,770 --> 01:47:25,354
...when I was trying
to tell you to listen?

1536
01:47:25,522 --> 01:47:28,482
That chap's run absolutely amok!

1537
01:47:29,651 --> 01:47:31,193
Few minutes, we'll have 'em in position.

1538
01:47:31,361 --> 01:47:34,196
In a couple of minutes,
we'll have you in position.

1539
01:47:34,364 --> 01:47:36,740
- You're doing a great job, Colonel.
- Thank you.

1540
01:47:36,908 --> 01:47:39,368
Why not just shoot 'em down?

1541
01:47:39,953 --> 01:47:42,872
None of these people must suspect...

1542
01:47:43,039 --> 01:47:45,875
...that they have ever been
under observation.

1543
01:47:46,960 --> 01:47:49,044
Now, none of them have ever seen me.

1544
01:47:49,212 --> 01:47:50,754
None of them know me...

1545
01:47:50,922 --> 01:47:53,632
...so I'll be moving in alone.

1546
01:47:54,885 --> 01:47:57,803
The minute I move in,
I'll give you the word.

1547
01:47:57,971 --> 01:47:59,972
And when you pass the word...

1548
01:48:01,224 --> 01:48:04,685
...I don't want to have another
policeman within miles of me.

1549
01:48:04,853 --> 01:48:06,228
- Right?
- Right.

1550
01:48:08,315 --> 01:48:10,608
I, uh...

1551
01:48:10,775 --> 01:48:14,236
I won't like it
if I see another policeman.

1552
01:48:15,780 --> 01:48:16,864
I give you my word.

1553
01:48:17,032 --> 01:48:20,576
I wanted to stop for you.
My wife and he wanted to stop for you.

1554
01:48:20,744 --> 01:48:23,037
Tell him how my mother-in-law
made us drive by him.

1555
01:48:23,205 --> 01:48:25,498
Anything you have to say
about your mother-in-law...

1556
01:48:25,665 --> 01:48:27,082
...you don't have to explain to me.

1557
01:48:27,250 --> 01:48:28,334
You know what I mean?

1558
01:48:28,502 --> 01:48:31,462
If she were a star
of a real crummy horror movie...

1559
01:48:31,630 --> 01:48:34,173
...I'd believe it.

1560
01:48:34,925 --> 01:48:35,841
Yeah!

1561
01:48:36,009 --> 01:48:37,051
That's him!

1562
01:48:37,219 --> 01:48:40,429
If I catch you, I'll kill you!
I tell you, I'll kill you!

1563
01:48:40,597 --> 01:48:42,765
You dirty robber!

1564
01:48:42,933 --> 01:48:44,558
Someone you know?

1565
01:49:00,116 --> 01:49:01,992
I'll drive. All set?

1566
01:49:02,160 --> 01:49:03,827
All set, Chief.

1567
01:49:03,995 --> 01:49:05,663
Culpeper, all set?

1568
01:49:05,830 --> 01:49:06,747
Yes, sir.

1569
01:49:06,915 --> 01:49:09,625
Airport just reported
and they're starting an approach now.

1570
01:49:09,793 --> 01:49:10,918
Right.

1571
01:49:18,802 --> 01:49:21,220
What's the matter, Chief?
You forgotten something?

1572
01:49:23,807 --> 01:49:26,392
No. I don't think
I've forgotten a thing.

1573
01:49:37,737 --> 01:49:42,032
Now, men, about the brakes...
You've got to know about the brakes.

1574
01:49:42,200 --> 01:49:46,328
I'll tell you
in just a minute. Just hold it a second.

1575
01:49:46,496 --> 01:49:48,747
What the hell is with this wire?

1576
01:49:48,915 --> 01:49:50,958
Just hold it a second.

1577
01:49:51,126 --> 01:49:52,501
What was that?

1578
01:49:52,669 --> 01:49:53,752
Men, look.

1579
01:49:53,920 --> 01:49:58,257
Be calm. This is it.
Just one minute more, it'll be all over.

1580
01:49:58,425 --> 01:50:00,968
I mean, it'll all be over.
I mean, courage, men.

1581
01:50:01,136 --> 01:50:04,179
We're all with you every second.

1582
01:50:04,347 --> 01:50:07,016
We're pulling for you
as hard as we can.

1583
01:50:07,183 --> 01:50:09,810
Now it's just hold onto
your nerves, men,

1584
01:50:09,978 --> 01:50:11,895
and not get excited
or do anything foolish.

1585
01:50:12,063 --> 01:50:14,356
But just keep calm.
That's all we'll do.

1586
01:50:14,524 --> 01:50:16,775
Keep calm. Calm, men!

1587
01:50:20,655 --> 01:50:22,364
Not that calm, you idiot!

1588
01:50:27,078 --> 01:50:28,954
Pull up!

1589
01:50:41,926 --> 01:50:44,011
Now, don't worry. Just keep calm.

1590
01:50:45,221 --> 01:50:47,890
What's this?
What's this that's coming?

1591
01:50:48,058 --> 01:50:52,519
- That's good. That's cement.
- What? Wait a minute! Hold it!

1592
01:50:52,687 --> 01:50:54,730
What are you doing, Benjy?

1593
01:51:00,737 --> 01:51:02,738
- What, are you trying to scare me?
- No!

1594
01:51:02,906 --> 01:51:04,406
Well, you did.

1595
01:51:06,868 --> 01:51:10,079
It's just a couple of sticks
of dynamite, that's all.

1596
01:51:10,246 --> 01:51:13,916
How much noise could it make?
Boom. It's all over.

1597
01:51:14,084 --> 01:51:15,918
Get it over right! Get it over!

1598
01:51:16,086 --> 01:51:17,086
Left rudder!

1599
01:51:17,253 --> 01:51:19,213
Too low! Pull up.

1600
01:51:19,381 --> 01:51:20,756
No! Left rudder!

1601
01:51:20,924 --> 01:51:24,051
No! Pull it up!

1602
01:51:24,219 --> 01:51:25,302
Help!

1603
01:51:27,389 --> 01:51:30,933
Help!
I'm the Colonel, you know!

1604
01:51:31,101 --> 01:51:32,101
Help!

1605
01:51:32,268 --> 01:51:34,645
Help! Get me down!

1606
01:51:37,607 --> 01:51:39,775
We're not going to land
and we'll never make it.

1607
01:51:39,943 --> 01:51:43,445
What do you mean, we'll never make it?
Don't freeze.

1608
01:51:43,613 --> 01:51:45,531
Benjy, don't freeze.

1609
01:51:49,661 --> 01:51:51,286
This one's going to work.

1610
01:51:51,454 --> 01:51:53,455
- Damn it, come to!
- You hit me.

1611
01:51:53,623 --> 01:51:56,375
Listen, wait a minute.

1612
01:52:02,841 --> 01:52:04,425
We're down!

1613
01:52:04,592 --> 01:52:06,468
- We're on the ground.
- Hooray!

1614
01:52:06,636 --> 01:52:09,722
It's just a noise, that's all.
It's way over there.

1615
01:52:14,394 --> 01:52:15,352
Put on the brakes.

1616
01:52:15,520 --> 01:52:16,895
Okay. Where are they?

1617
01:52:17,063 --> 01:52:19,189
Benjy! Here comes a restaurant!

1618
01:52:26,948 --> 01:52:28,532
We've landed! Come on.

1619
01:52:34,789 --> 01:52:37,374
Come on. Hurry. Now, hurry up.

1620
01:52:37,542 --> 01:52:39,543
- Come on, let's go.
- What about him?

1621
01:52:39,711 --> 01:52:41,754
Never mind him.
An ambulance will come.

1622
01:52:41,921 --> 01:52:43,714
Let's get out of here.

1623
01:52:45,550 --> 01:52:47,551
Cab!

1624
01:52:48,094 --> 01:52:50,763
Cab!

1625
01:52:51,222 --> 01:52:54,141
We're in an awful hurry.
Do you know where the State Park is?

1626
01:52:54,309 --> 01:52:56,226
Sure. What happened?

1627
01:52:56,394 --> 01:52:58,103
Emergency landing. Come on, hurry.

1628
01:52:58,271 --> 01:53:00,022
Quick, let's go. Come on.

1629
01:53:00,190 --> 01:53:01,607
Come on, Benjy.

1630
01:53:14,287 --> 01:53:16,830
Oh! Excuse me.

1631
01:53:21,795 --> 01:53:23,712
Excuse us. Here's your bag.

1632
01:53:25,298 --> 01:53:27,466
You see, the lock didn't work.

1633
01:53:27,634 --> 01:53:28,550
Go.

1634
01:53:28,718 --> 01:53:32,638
That's all.
The owners will pay for everything.

1635
01:53:32,806 --> 01:53:35,140
Next door, he'll pay for everything.
It's okay.

1636
01:53:43,775 --> 01:53:45,275
You people. You!

1637
01:53:45,443 --> 01:53:47,402
Come back here. Come back!

1638
01:53:47,570 --> 01:53:49,363
You vandals!

1639
01:53:49,531 --> 01:53:52,908
The cops in this town
are morons, retarded.

1640
01:53:53,076 --> 01:53:54,910
I'm dealing with moronic people.

1641
01:53:55,078 --> 01:53:57,412
'Cause he's in a bad humor,
that fat Nazi.

1642
01:53:57,580 --> 01:53:59,206
What, I gotta suffer 'cause of him?

1643
01:53:59,374 --> 01:54:01,959
Get away from me.
What's the matter?

1644
01:54:02,126 --> 01:54:06,588
Can't you see I'm on the phone?
Gimme two minutes!

1645
01:54:06,756 --> 01:54:08,382
Now, listen, Sy...

1646
01:54:09,008 --> 01:54:11,426
Will you take us
to Santa Rosita State Park?

1647
01:54:11,594 --> 01:54:14,137
What's the matter?
What happened to you? Initiation?

1648
01:54:14,305 --> 01:54:16,098
We had an accident. Hurry up!

1649
01:54:16,933 --> 01:54:19,560
Benjamin and Bell stopped
at a gardener supply place

1650
01:54:19,727 --> 01:54:21,687
and bought picks and shovels.

1651
01:54:21,855 --> 01:54:24,398
Hold it, Chief.
Here's a report on the Crumps.

1652
01:54:24,566 --> 01:54:28,944
Their cab turned onto 101 moving south
toward your present position.

1653
01:54:29,112 --> 01:54:33,156
Wait. The other taxi's
also turning onto 101...

1654
01:54:33,324 --> 01:54:36,368
...and they're moving north.
They're both coming your way.

1655
01:54:36,536 --> 01:54:37,619
Understood.

1656
01:54:37,787 --> 01:54:39,121
Stand by.

1657
01:54:39,289 --> 01:54:42,249
- They ought to be here any minute.
- Uh-huh.

1658
01:55:05,815 --> 01:55:07,065
Look.

1659
01:55:07,233 --> 01:55:10,944
It's the two idiots, the little one and
the one with the marbles in his mouth.

1660
01:55:11,112 --> 01:55:13,864
- It's that hokey dentist.
- Yeah.

1661
01:55:14,032 --> 01:55:15,240
Pass that cab.

1662
01:55:15,408 --> 01:55:17,075
- What's the rush?
- Whaddaya mean "rush"?

1663
01:55:17,243 --> 01:55:19,620
No rush. We're just in a hurry.

1664
01:55:28,129 --> 01:55:29,671
Culpeper.

1665
01:55:29,839 --> 01:55:31,340
Now.

1666
01:55:31,507 --> 01:55:33,342
Give the order to pull away.

1667
01:55:39,682 --> 01:55:42,059
- Come on. Hurry up.
- Shouldn't I wait around?

1668
01:55:42,226 --> 01:55:43,185
No. Here's $5.

1669
01:55:43,353 --> 01:55:46,980
- What's with the pick and shovel?
- Mind your own business. Come on.

1670
01:55:48,274 --> 01:55:52,319
Hey! Hey!

1671
01:55:53,196 --> 01:55:55,072
- Think anybody is here?
- Didn't see any cars.

1672
01:55:55,239 --> 01:55:56,907
Wait a minute!

1673
01:55:57,450 --> 01:55:59,868
- Let's talk this over.
- I got nothing to talk about.

1674
01:56:00,036 --> 01:56:01,662
Wait a minute.

1675
01:56:01,829 --> 01:56:03,205
Think anybody else has been here?

1676
01:56:03,373 --> 01:56:05,624
- How should I know?
- Wait!

1677
01:56:05,792 --> 01:56:08,543
If you think we're the first ones here,
why not make a deal?

1678
01:56:08,711 --> 01:56:09,670
The four of us?

1679
01:56:09,837 --> 01:56:12,172
Nobody knows where to look,
so we'll look together.

1680
01:56:12,340 --> 01:56:16,885
We'll find it before the others.
Incidentally, where are all the others?

1681
01:56:17,053 --> 01:56:20,722
How come you two just got here?
You had the plane.

1682
01:56:20,890 --> 01:56:24,393
Yeah... What happened to you?

1683
01:56:24,560 --> 01:56:27,229
They're up to something funny,
you hear?

1684
01:56:27,397 --> 01:56:31,233
Did you see the blonde I brought,
covered in paint with her dress ripped?

1685
01:56:31,401 --> 01:56:32,943
What's that all about?

1686
01:56:33,111 --> 01:56:36,738
Yeah. And what about
the picks and shovels?

1687
01:56:45,498 --> 01:56:48,959
You run back to headquarters.
Wait till you hear from me.

1688
01:56:49,127 --> 01:56:50,252
Let me come, Chief.

1689
01:56:50,420 --> 01:56:53,130
I'd like to,
but it might snarl things up.

1690
01:56:54,173 --> 01:56:56,091
Thanks for everything.

1691
01:56:56,259 --> 01:56:58,051
Lots of luck, Chief.

1692
01:57:32,795 --> 01:57:35,756
Benjy! Did you see anything, pal?

1693
01:57:35,923 --> 01:57:38,341
No, but there must be
something somewhere.

1694
01:57:38,509 --> 01:57:41,178
Yeah... Hey! Hey!

1695
01:57:42,513 --> 01:57:44,139
- See anything?
- Not a thing.

1696
01:57:44,307 --> 01:57:47,476
Are you sure he didn't say
something you've forgotten?

1697
01:57:47,643 --> 01:57:51,396
He said it's buried under a big W
and that we'd see it.

1698
01:57:51,564 --> 01:57:53,815
- It's gotta be here.
- I tell you what we do.

1699
01:57:53,983 --> 01:57:56,193
You go how we came.
We'll go how you came.

1700
01:57:56,360 --> 01:57:58,737
We might have missed something.
Hold it.

1701
01:57:59,822 --> 01:58:01,782
You go the way we came...

1702
01:58:01,949 --> 01:58:03,867
That's right. Okay, let's go.

1703
01:58:11,501 --> 01:58:14,002
They're looking for something
buried under a big W.

1704
01:58:14,170 --> 01:58:16,880
I heard one of them,
the stutterer, say it.

1705
01:58:17,048 --> 01:58:19,382
Yeah, I heard. But what?

1706
01:59:07,849 --> 01:59:09,057
Hey!

1707
01:59:09,225 --> 01:59:10,517
Did you see anything?

1708
01:59:10,685 --> 01:59:11,977
- No. Did you?
- Nothing.

1709
01:59:12,145 --> 01:59:14,729
That guy hid it so good,
he couldn't find it himself.

1710
01:59:14,897 --> 01:59:15,897
I think...

1711
01:59:26,075 --> 01:59:27,242
Who's he?

1712
01:59:27,410 --> 01:59:30,078
- I don't know.
- But he had a shovel.

1713
01:59:30,246 --> 01:59:31,705
Maybe he's a prospector.

1714
01:59:31,873 --> 01:59:33,957
- What are you talking...
- We're wasting time.

1715
01:59:34,125 --> 01:59:35,876
Harder. We gotta look harder!

1716
01:59:36,043 --> 01:59:38,336
Let's look harder. Come on, let's go.

1717
01:59:50,600 --> 01:59:51,600
Who's he?

1718
01:59:51,767 --> 01:59:53,935
I don't know,
but he hasn't got a shovel.

1719
02:00:02,278 --> 02:00:04,529
- He's here, I tell ya.
- Yes, sir. That's his car.

1720
02:00:04,697 --> 02:00:07,574
- I'll get that phony.
- Somebody must've come in those cabs.

1721
02:00:07,742 --> 02:00:11,203
- Come on, let's get moving!
- Come on, let's get moving!

1722
02:00:11,370 --> 02:00:14,289
- They must be here.
- They'd better be. Come on, Emmeline.

1723
02:00:14,457 --> 02:00:17,083
- Don't just sit there!
- Don't just sit there!

1724
02:00:17,251 --> 02:00:19,044
Yes, I am.

1725
02:00:19,212 --> 02:00:21,296
Then sit!

1726
02:00:21,464 --> 02:00:24,174
Mrs. Finch,
aren't you the teeniest bit curious?

1727
02:00:24,342 --> 02:00:28,386
No. I'm not even curious,
just disgusted.

1728
02:00:28,554 --> 02:00:32,224
I say, that really is a pity.
Do forgive me, I must go.

1729
02:00:39,523 --> 02:00:41,816
Psst!

1730
02:00:41,984 --> 02:00:44,319
You wouldn't know a big W
if you saw one!

1731
02:00:44,487 --> 02:00:45,820
- I know a...
- Shut up!

1732
02:00:45,988 --> 02:00:48,865
I don't care what you say,
I don't think they're here yet.

1733
02:00:49,033 --> 02:00:51,660
They're here somewhere.
That means they haven't found it.

1734
02:00:51,827 --> 02:00:53,995
That's all he said? "Under a big W"?

1735
02:00:54,163 --> 02:00:56,456
Actually, I joined the party after that.

1736
02:00:56,624 --> 02:00:59,000
Yes, sir, that's what he said.
It's under a big W.

1737
02:00:59,168 --> 02:01:02,671
- Let's look...
- Will you shut up and follow me?

1738
02:01:56,976 --> 02:01:58,268
- Who's that?
- I don't know!

1739
02:01:58,436 --> 02:02:00,228
- From this morning?
- Yes.

1740
02:02:02,898 --> 02:02:05,066
- Who's he?
- I don't know.

1741
02:02:06,610 --> 02:02:08,194
- Who's he?
- I don't know!

1742
02:02:08,362 --> 02:02:11,281
Mama, how many people
are mixed up in this?

1743
02:02:12,450 --> 02:02:15,118
Mama, who are they? Cabbies?

1744
02:02:15,286 --> 02:02:17,203
Mama, this thing's like a convention.

1745
02:02:54,408 --> 02:02:57,077
Is anything wrong, ma'am?
I didn't mean to startle you.

1746
02:02:57,244 --> 02:03:00,997
Who are you? Are you with the others,
the ones that are looking?

1747
02:03:01,165 --> 02:03:03,500
- I am, in a way. Aren't you?
- No.

1748
02:03:03,667 --> 02:03:06,753
I mean, I didn't want anything
to do with it right from the start.

1749
02:03:06,921 --> 02:03:08,797
And you know what?

1750
02:03:08,964 --> 02:03:13,468
I know where it is. I'm the only one,
and I wasn't even looking.

1751
02:03:13,636 --> 02:03:14,928
You know where it is?

1752
02:03:15,096 --> 02:03:17,138
Yes! What should I do?

1753
02:03:18,724 --> 02:03:20,683
Ugh!

1754
02:03:20,851 --> 02:03:22,852
Come on out, everyone!
This is ridiculous.

1755
02:03:23,020 --> 02:03:25,355
- I absolutely agree.
- Come on out.

1756
02:03:25,523 --> 02:03:27,982
We all know we're all here.
Nobody's fooling anyone.

1757
02:03:28,150 --> 02:03:29,651
So we all know. So what?

1758
02:03:29,819 --> 02:03:31,986
Don't talk to my mama
in that tone of voice!

1759
02:03:32,154 --> 02:03:33,488
- You hear?
- Shut up!

1760
02:03:33,656 --> 02:03:37,534
Listen, we ain't the only ones here.
I seen four or five others.

1761
02:03:37,701 --> 02:03:39,160
Those two cab drivers.

1762
02:03:39,328 --> 02:03:42,330
- They came with us and that dentist.
- You want to start?

1763
02:03:42,498 --> 02:03:45,667
- Yes, I want to...
- Why are we wasting time?

1764
02:03:45,835 --> 02:03:47,210
We're all here.

1765
02:03:47,378 --> 02:03:50,880
Even if somebody finds the money,
nobody gets away with it...

1766
02:03:51,048 --> 02:03:53,091
...unless everybody gets a share.

1767
02:03:53,259 --> 02:03:56,136
Let's all get sensible
and get this organized.

1768
02:03:56,303 --> 02:03:59,013
Did you all hear what Mama said?

1769
02:03:59,181 --> 02:04:01,724
- Come on, Mama.
- Now, wait a minute.

1770
02:04:01,892 --> 02:04:05,019
Did any of you see a guy with glasses...

1771
02:04:05,187 --> 02:04:07,814
...with a sneery expression on his face?

1772
02:04:07,982 --> 02:04:11,151
This guy was ugly.
I mean, like, real ugly.

1773
02:04:15,197 --> 02:04:19,742
If you help dig it up,
you can have half and I'll have half.

1774
02:04:19,910 --> 02:04:22,537
Is that okay? I mean, is that fair?

1775
02:04:23,289 --> 02:04:25,582
If I have half of the money...

1776
02:04:25,749 --> 02:04:29,043
...I can go away somewhere
where nobody can find me.

1777
02:04:29,211 --> 02:04:34,215
Not Russell or my mother
or Sylvester, anybody.

1778
02:04:35,176 --> 02:04:37,427
You don't know what that'd mean.

1779
02:04:37,595 --> 02:04:38,887
If I had enough money...

1780
02:04:39,054 --> 02:04:42,432
...I might be able to live
in a convent or something.

1781
02:04:42,600 --> 02:04:44,559
- In a convent?
- Uh-huh.

1782
02:04:44,727 --> 02:04:47,395
We all know we're all here.

1783
02:04:47,563 --> 02:04:50,565
It seems intelligent to me
that we should all share...

1784
02:04:50,733 --> 02:04:52,859
...in one equal share apiece, right?

1785
02:04:53,027 --> 02:04:54,068
Right. Mel was right.

1786
02:04:54,236 --> 02:04:56,779
We all know that. Lookit...

1787
02:04:56,947 --> 02:04:59,532
- Oh, no.
- Oh, yeah. Mm-hm.

1788
02:04:59,700 --> 02:05:01,993
It's him, all right. Yeah!

1789
02:05:02,953 --> 02:05:06,080
You got this wrong.
I came to apologize.

1790
02:05:06,248 --> 02:05:09,375
Forgive and forget! I'm your friend.

1791
02:05:09,543 --> 02:05:11,920
He's so neurotic.
Can't you do something?

1792
02:05:12,087 --> 02:05:12,879
I'll get you.

1793
02:05:13,047 --> 02:05:17,342
- He's very neurotic. I'm your friend!
- When I get my hands on you...

1794
02:05:29,396 --> 02:05:30,480
Why, that's it.

1795
02:05:30,648 --> 02:05:32,607
Sure. Look!

1796
02:05:32,775 --> 02:05:34,859
It's the big W, I tell you!

1797
02:05:35,027 --> 02:05:37,362
It's the big W!

1798
02:05:39,615 --> 02:05:40,532
Look at this.

1799
02:05:40,699 --> 02:05:43,284
Look at it!

1800
02:05:47,957 --> 02:05:49,749
I'm sorry, Mrs. Finch.

1801
02:05:51,168 --> 02:05:53,336
I'm afraid it's too late.

1802
02:05:53,504 --> 02:05:55,463
I think they've found it.

1803
02:05:57,007 --> 02:05:59,968
Right here all the time!
He wasn't kidding!

1804
02:06:00,135 --> 02:06:04,305
- He was telling the truth!
- Folks, isn't this great?

1805
02:06:04,974 --> 02:06:07,767
Congratulations. Well done.

1806
02:06:07,935 --> 02:06:11,479
Listen, I think the big boy
should get an extra share.

1807
02:06:11,647 --> 02:06:13,690
After all, it was he who found it.

1808
02:06:13,857 --> 02:06:17,110
Yes! I insist he gets an extra share.

1809
02:06:17,278 --> 02:06:19,571
That's right.
He deserves an extra share.

1810
02:06:19,738 --> 02:06:22,323
- Well, I...
- Let's start digging.

1811
02:06:22,491 --> 02:06:24,659
Suppose somebody comes along.
What do we tell him?

1812
02:06:24,827 --> 02:06:27,579
We're here with
an anthropological expedition.

1813
02:06:27,746 --> 02:06:29,455
- Nah.
- We don't tell them anything!

1814
02:06:29,623 --> 02:06:32,041
We tell them to scram
or we beat their brains in.

1815
02:06:32,835 --> 02:06:34,752
It was a nice dream.

1816
02:06:36,005 --> 02:06:37,922
Lasted almost five minutes.

1817
02:06:47,933 --> 02:06:50,143
Now, don't bug me, I said.

1818
02:06:50,311 --> 02:06:52,061
Faster.

1819
02:06:52,229 --> 02:06:53,938
Come on, dig, dig.

1820
02:06:54,106 --> 02:06:56,149
Faster, faster.

1821
02:06:56,317 --> 02:06:58,985
Faster. Dig. That's it, dig.

1822
02:07:54,083 --> 02:07:55,124
Faster.

1823
02:08:08,764 --> 02:08:11,849
There's not enough room.
You two, out.

1824
02:08:12,017 --> 02:08:13,601
Let us do it.

1825
02:08:19,942 --> 02:08:23,444
Wait. There's not enough room.
You're bugging me.

1826
02:08:23,612 --> 02:08:25,697
- "Bugging"?
- Cut out, cut out.

1827
02:08:25,864 --> 02:08:27,156
What's this "cut out" talk?

1828
02:08:27,324 --> 02:08:29,575
- Out, baby. Out!
- Don't call me baby.

1829
02:08:29,743 --> 02:08:33,371
- Quit arguing!
- Will ya come on?

1830
02:08:44,174 --> 02:08:46,551
- What's that?
- What was that?

1831
02:08:47,970 --> 02:08:49,679
- That's it.
- Sounded like a chest.

1832
02:08:49,847 --> 02:08:52,056
I wonder what's in it.

1833
02:08:52,224 --> 02:08:53,725
Bring it up here!

1834
02:09:00,899 --> 02:09:02,984
There it is!

1835
02:09:03,152 --> 02:09:04,986
- It's a satchel.
- Hold it up!

1836
02:09:06,488 --> 02:09:09,699
- It's a satchel!
- I got it.

1837
02:09:10,743 --> 02:09:11,993
Open it up.

1838
02:09:12,161 --> 02:09:13,494
Come on!

1839
02:09:15,831 --> 02:09:17,623
Bingo!

1840
02:09:18,417 --> 02:09:21,502
I say, chaps,
shouldn't we find a spot of cover?

1841
02:09:21,670 --> 02:09:22,837
There's nobody around.

1842
02:09:23,005 --> 02:09:24,505
Come on. Count it out.

1843
02:09:24,673 --> 02:09:26,966
- What are we waiting for?
- Now wait a second!

1844
02:09:27,134 --> 02:09:31,345
Everybody's going to get something, so
no arguments. We all get equal shares!

1845
02:09:31,513 --> 02:09:32,680
He's right.

1846
02:09:32,848 --> 02:09:35,767
That's the only way to do it.
Shares for everybody.

1847
02:09:35,934 --> 02:09:38,060
Now, how many are we?

1848
02:09:38,228 --> 02:09:40,104
One, two...

1849
02:09:40,272 --> 02:09:44,567
...three, four, five,
six, seven, eight...

1850
02:09:45,444 --> 02:09:50,198
...9, 10, 11, 12, 13...

1851
02:09:50,365 --> 02:09:52,575
...14, 15.

1852
02:09:52,743 --> 02:09:55,369
15 of us. That means 15 equal shares.

1853
02:09:55,537 --> 02:09:59,123
You dirty double-crosser.
You cut yourself in for twice!

1854
02:09:59,291 --> 02:10:01,334
You can't get away with that!

1855
02:10:01,710 --> 02:10:02,794
Get him!

1856
02:10:02,961 --> 02:10:04,212
Grab him!

1857
02:10:04,379 --> 02:10:05,755
Get him!

1858
02:10:07,841 --> 02:10:11,344
You only cheated yourself
because now you're out.

1859
02:10:11,512 --> 02:10:15,181
Listen!
You can't cut me out now, you hear?

1860
02:10:15,349 --> 02:10:17,099
Not after what I've been through!

1861
02:10:18,060 --> 02:10:19,560
All right. Okay.

1862
02:10:19,728 --> 02:10:23,856
I'm warning you, if I don't get a share,
I'm going straight to the police.

1863
02:10:24,024 --> 02:10:27,276
- The police?
- What makes you think the police...

1864
02:10:27,986 --> 02:10:30,154
That money had to come from somewhere.

1865
02:10:30,322 --> 02:10:34,742
We know where it's from,
that poor man that died on the mountain.

1866
02:10:34,910 --> 02:10:37,328
You wasn't even there, so shut up.

1867
02:10:37,496 --> 02:10:40,873
Okay, you asked for it.
I'm going straight to the police.

1868
02:10:41,041 --> 02:10:43,543
You think they'd be interested,
Mr. Meyer?

1869
02:10:43,710 --> 02:10:46,128
Are you kidding? Isn't it obvious?

1870
02:10:46,296 --> 02:10:47,922
How do you think money gets...

1871
02:10:51,301 --> 02:10:52,760
How did you know my name?

1872
02:10:52,928 --> 02:10:54,345
You know this crook?

1873
02:10:54,513 --> 02:10:59,475
I've never met him, Mr. Pike,
but I've come to feel that I know him.

1874
02:11:00,435 --> 02:11:03,437
How did you know my name?
I've never met you.

1875
02:11:03,605 --> 02:11:06,357
Yeah, who are you?

1876
02:11:06,525 --> 02:11:08,067
Didn't he come with you?

1877
02:11:08,235 --> 02:11:11,153
He didn't come with us.
We thought he came with you.

1878
02:11:11,321 --> 02:11:12,613
No.

1879
02:11:12,781 --> 02:11:16,993
If he didn't come with us,
then who are you?

1880
02:11:17,870 --> 02:11:19,954
I'm Capt. Culpeper...

1881
02:11:20,122 --> 02:11:22,248
...of the Santa Rosita
Police Department.

1882
02:11:27,754 --> 02:11:30,256
- Will you come to the point?
- Yeah, I'm coming to it.

1883
02:11:30,424 --> 02:11:34,135
Point is, I have enough stuff
in my private files...

1884
02:11:34,303 --> 02:11:36,470
...stuff relating to civic building...

1885
02:11:36,638 --> 02:11:39,891
...road contracts,
harbor and cannery projects...

1886
02:11:40,058 --> 02:11:42,810
...enough stuff to put you,
the D.A., myself...

1887
02:11:42,978 --> 02:11:47,315
...and a two-thirds majority behind bars
for the next 20 years.

1888
02:11:47,482 --> 02:11:51,485
And I give you my word, that's
exactly where everybody's going...

1889
02:11:51,653 --> 02:11:56,032
...unless things start happening now.
- Like what, for instance?

1890
02:11:56,199 --> 02:11:59,285
I want the pension
for Culpeper's grade trebled.

1891
02:11:59,453 --> 02:12:03,748
Not doubled, trebled.
I want Culpeper to retire with honor.

1892
02:12:03,916 --> 02:12:08,002
I want it on paper that
that's exactly what's going to happen.

1893
02:12:08,170 --> 02:12:10,963
And I want it in my hands
in 15 minutes...

1894
02:12:11,131 --> 02:12:14,091
...or I'll have all the reporters
in town in here in 20.

1895
02:12:14,843 --> 02:12:19,096
You know the word for this, Your Honor.
It's called blackmail.

1896
02:12:37,324 --> 02:12:41,077
Sir, could you possibly see
your way clear to give us a break?

1897
02:12:41,244 --> 02:12:43,329
You kidding? Him give you a break?

1898
02:12:43,497 --> 02:12:46,290
We had a pretty rough day already.

1899
02:12:46,458 --> 02:12:50,044
We was all covered with dirt,
and we fell down in an airplane...

1900
02:12:50,212 --> 02:12:52,838
...and my grandmother's dying in Oxnard.

1901
02:12:53,006 --> 02:12:55,216
I know we don't deserve
any kindness, Captain.

1902
02:12:55,384 --> 02:12:59,345
But if you could help us,
I'm sure we'd all be inspired...

1903
02:12:59,513 --> 02:13:01,222
...to live better lives.

1904
02:13:01,390 --> 02:13:03,474
Well, there is one thing.

1905
02:13:04,434 --> 02:13:06,769
I don't know
whether it would help or not.

1906
02:13:06,937 --> 02:13:11,273
But if, instead of my turning you in...

1907
02:13:11,441 --> 02:13:13,901
...you went and turned yourselves in...

1908
02:13:14,069 --> 02:13:17,905
...juries sometimes look very favorably
on things like that.

1909
02:13:18,073 --> 02:13:20,574
You'd let us do that?

1910
02:13:20,742 --> 02:13:23,160
What are we waiting for?
Let's turn ourselves in.

1911
02:13:23,328 --> 02:13:24,912
You must be a fine human being.

1912
02:13:25,080 --> 02:13:27,832
After all, why should you worry
whether we get a break?

1913
02:13:28,000 --> 02:13:31,085
Well, Mr. Meyer,
no matter what you've all done today...

1914
02:13:31,253 --> 02:13:34,422
...you're not really criminals.

1915
02:13:34,589 --> 02:13:37,508
So if you like,
you can all hop into those two cabs...

1916
02:13:37,676 --> 02:13:40,720
...and drive over to Santa Rosita...

1917
02:13:40,887 --> 02:13:44,098
...and, uh, just walk in.

1918
02:13:44,266 --> 02:13:47,768
- Then let's do that.
- But, sir, we can't all fit.

1919
02:13:47,936 --> 02:13:52,231
You can't take the stolen vehicles.
Those have to stay to be picked up.

1920
02:13:52,399 --> 02:13:55,192
- What are we waiting for?
- Let's go.

1921
02:13:57,112 --> 02:13:58,779
Back in the back.

1922
02:14:01,992 --> 02:14:03,034
Drive carefully.

1923
02:14:03,201 --> 02:14:05,745
They may be the last passengers
you'll ever carry.

1924
02:14:05,912 --> 02:14:07,413
Funny. That's funny.

1925
02:14:07,581 --> 02:14:08,789
Funny, right? Funny?

1926
02:14:08,957 --> 02:14:11,792
You could be the most
comical cop I ever met.

1927
02:14:11,960 --> 02:14:13,085
Yeah.

1928
02:14:40,489 --> 02:14:42,823
- Culpeper.
- Yes, sir.

1929
02:14:43,450 --> 02:14:45,785
Everything is under control here.

1930
02:14:45,952 --> 02:14:49,038
It'll take a little longer
because there was a joker in the deck...

1931
02:14:49,206 --> 02:14:51,665
...that nobody knew about. All right?

1932
02:14:51,833 --> 02:14:53,375
Yes, sir.

1933
02:14:53,543 --> 02:14:56,712
So don't make a move of any kind
until you hear from me.

1934
02:14:56,880 --> 02:14:57,922
Yes, sir.

1935
02:15:04,763 --> 02:15:08,766
Listen, why does the man
want to give everybody a break?

1936
02:15:08,934 --> 02:15:11,894
- What's his angle there?
- I was wondering about that, too.

1937
02:15:12,062 --> 02:15:15,689
Something funny's going on.
How's he know what we're going to do?

1938
02:15:15,857 --> 02:15:18,317
We're in enough of a mess.
We better do what he said.

1939
02:15:18,485 --> 02:15:20,861
I'm tellin' you,
the man has got some angle.

1940
02:15:21,029 --> 02:15:22,613
Wait, wait. Hold it!

1941
02:15:22,781 --> 02:15:24,073
Can you see him?

1942
02:15:34,126 --> 02:15:37,753
- Just what does he think he's doing?
- That certainly is strange.

1943
02:15:37,921 --> 02:15:40,005
- Sure is.
- What is he doing?

1944
02:15:40,173 --> 02:15:43,384
- He's going the other way.
- Why are we standing here?

1945
02:15:43,552 --> 02:15:46,470
That's it!

1946
02:15:46,638 --> 02:15:48,889
We're off the hook!

1947
02:15:49,558 --> 02:15:52,226
Get out of here! Come on, we're off!

1948
02:15:52,394 --> 02:15:54,061
Come on, get going.

1949
02:16:06,741 --> 02:16:09,577
- Ah!
- Holy mackerel. Almost didn't make it.

1950
02:16:24,676 --> 02:16:27,094
No other cops around. He planned it.

1951
02:16:27,262 --> 02:16:31,140
We found the money and he was waiting
to take it away from us.

1952
02:16:31,308 --> 02:16:35,603
But if we all find the money first
and turn it in, we're all in the clear.

1953
02:16:35,770 --> 02:16:38,939
Let's just get the dough
and worry about the rest later.

1954
02:16:39,107 --> 02:16:42,401
- Look. He's slowing down.
- No, he's turning to the left.

1955
02:17:35,121 --> 02:17:36,830
What's going on?

1956
02:17:36,998 --> 02:17:38,457
Sorry, Jimmy.

1957
02:18:30,343 --> 02:18:32,261
He's heading for the border!

1958
02:18:32,429 --> 02:18:34,430
We should stop
and call the police station!

1959
02:18:34,597 --> 02:18:35,723
You shut up!

1960
02:18:35,890 --> 02:18:38,726
We're going to get that money.
Keep driving!

1961
02:18:38,893 --> 02:18:41,228
That woman is something else.

1962
02:18:41,396 --> 02:18:43,230
Take your foot off the brake!

1963
02:18:43,398 --> 02:18:44,898
Stop hitting me. I'm driving.

1964
02:18:45,066 --> 02:18:48,402
- When you want a cab, you can't get one.
- Yeah, come on, let's go!

1965
02:18:57,412 --> 02:18:59,413
F-14 to Central.

1966
02:18:59,581 --> 02:19:00,998
Come in. What is it?

1967
02:19:01,166 --> 02:19:02,750
There's something phony here.

1968
02:19:02,917 --> 02:19:05,794
We're on 101 by Cortez
checking a mad-dog report.

1969
02:19:05,962 --> 02:19:07,755
Orders were to maintain silence.

1970
02:19:07,922 --> 02:19:10,215
Capt. Culpeper wants
this channel kept clear.

1971
02:19:10,383 --> 02:19:12,092
We know it,
but we saw Capt. Culpeper.

1972
02:19:12,260 --> 02:19:15,304
He just went by doing 90 miles an hour.

1973
02:19:16,181 --> 02:19:18,474
I don't think I understand that.

1974
02:19:19,100 --> 02:19:20,934
Are you sure it was Capt. Culpeper?

1975
02:19:21,102 --> 02:19:23,103
- Yep.
- Was he chasing anybody?

1976
02:19:23,271 --> 02:19:25,814
- Nope.
- Could he have been chasing anybody?

1977
02:19:25,982 --> 02:19:29,026
Not a chance.
That's what struck us so funny.

1978
02:19:29,194 --> 02:19:32,237
There were about 15 people
in two cabs behind him.

1979
02:19:32,405 --> 02:19:34,281
It looked like they were chasing him.

1980
02:19:34,449 --> 02:19:37,534
They were chasing him?
What's going on here?

1981
02:19:37,702 --> 02:19:39,870
I brought it myself.
Everything you asked for.

1982
02:19:40,038 --> 02:19:41,288
- The pension?
- Yeah.

1983
02:19:41,456 --> 02:19:43,874
Call Capt. Culpeper.

1984
02:19:44,042 --> 02:19:47,002
Calling Capt. Culpeper.
Central Division. Urgent.

1985
02:19:47,170 --> 02:19:49,963
Calling Capt. Culpeper.

1986
02:19:58,431 --> 02:20:02,351
- This can only happen in America.
- You going to start that again?

1987
02:20:33,508 --> 02:20:36,885
You've got to believe me.
I'm going to be sick.

1988
02:21:49,542 --> 02:21:52,211
What's the matter?
You trying to kill us?

1989
02:21:52,378 --> 02:21:55,339
Just don't make me nervous!

1990
02:22:29,791 --> 02:22:32,918
- Don't let him get away!
- Cut him off!

1991
02:22:37,757 --> 02:22:41,802
Calling Capt. Culpeper.
Culp, this is Aloysius speaking.

1992
02:22:41,970 --> 02:22:45,472
Now, listen to me, Culp.
Everything has been fixed.

1993
02:22:45,640 --> 02:22:48,308
There's been negotiations
and everything is all right.

1994
02:22:48,476 --> 02:22:51,019
Cut out this nonsense and answer me.

1995
02:22:51,187 --> 02:22:53,188
This is Aloysius speaking.

1996
02:23:03,616 --> 02:23:07,744
I still don't understand this.
What's it all about?

1997
02:23:07,912 --> 02:23:10,289
Um... That's it.

1998
02:23:12,667 --> 02:23:14,209
All units...

1999
02:23:14,377 --> 02:23:16,128
...arrest Capt. Culpeper.

2000
02:23:18,047 --> 02:23:20,173
There he is!

2001
02:23:25,471 --> 02:23:28,223
- Come back!
- Get me out of here!

2002
02:23:28,391 --> 02:23:30,601
Just don't sit there. Come on.

2003
02:23:33,146 --> 02:23:34,271
Come on!

2004
02:23:45,533 --> 02:23:47,367
Stop pushing, will ya?

2005
02:23:47,827 --> 02:23:51,121
Wait. We got him.
Now, you women stay here.

2006
02:23:51,289 --> 02:23:53,165
What do you mean,
"You women stay here"?

2007
02:23:53,333 --> 02:23:54,875
You heard him, mother. Stay here!

2008
02:23:55,043 --> 02:23:56,668
Come on! Let's go!

2009
02:24:12,435 --> 02:24:15,771
- Is he there?
- Where'd he go?

2010
02:24:15,938 --> 02:24:17,439
Halt! Halt!

2011
02:24:17,607 --> 02:24:19,524
Now, wait a minute. Listen.

2012
02:24:28,785 --> 02:24:31,411
Yeah!

2013
02:25:36,477 --> 02:25:39,312
Stop pushing! Get the suitcase.

2014
02:25:41,149 --> 02:25:42,899
Look! Look up there!

2015
02:25:43,067 --> 02:25:45,277
...in this regard,
and there is no doubt...

2016
02:25:46,487 --> 02:25:48,655
Hey! Hey!

2017
02:25:51,659 --> 02:25:53,285
Those ladders are not safe!

2018
02:25:53,453 --> 02:25:56,663
Ladders are not safe!

2019
02:26:02,670 --> 02:26:04,796
Get off!

2020
02:26:04,964 --> 02:26:06,840
- You got it?
- Get it away.

2021
02:26:14,015 --> 02:26:15,974
Get moving!

2022
02:26:16,142 --> 02:26:18,018
Don't push. You got it? That's it.

2023
02:26:24,192 --> 02:26:27,694
Sylvester, what are you doing up there?
You must be out of your mind!

2024
02:26:31,199 --> 02:26:34,075
- Wait a minute!
- Get the suitcase!

2025
02:26:39,040 --> 02:26:40,499
Get that money!

2026
02:27:01,229 --> 02:27:03,730
Don't you dare touch any of that money.

2027
02:27:16,369 --> 02:27:19,371
- You! Don't stand there!
- To your right!

2028
02:27:31,175 --> 02:27:32,634
Russell, hang on!

2029
02:27:36,430 --> 02:27:38,306
Dingy, I can't hold on!

2030
02:27:40,434 --> 02:27:41,643
Help us!

2031
02:27:45,231 --> 02:27:47,023
Get off my hand!

2032
02:28:07,962 --> 02:28:09,754
Move onto the ladder!

2033
02:28:11,132 --> 02:28:15,635
Hold on! Wait a minute!
One at a time! Did you hear me?

2034
02:28:15,803 --> 02:28:17,053
One at a time!

2035
02:28:20,141 --> 02:28:21,725
All right!

2036
02:28:21,893 --> 02:28:24,895
All right, you'll see. You'll see.

2037
02:28:26,439 --> 02:28:29,316
Get on alphabetical. I'm Benjy.

2038
02:28:29,483 --> 02:28:32,360
Quit stepping on my head!

2039
02:28:32,528 --> 02:28:36,156
Get on the ladder.

2040
02:28:36,324 --> 02:28:38,658
Don't leave me! Come back here!

2041
02:28:38,826 --> 02:28:40,577
You can't leave me!

2042
02:28:46,959 --> 02:28:49,544
There's too many men
on it to control it.

2043
02:29:18,824 --> 02:29:21,534
Hold it steady. Watch it.
She's whipping loose.

2044
02:29:54,527 --> 02:29:56,111
Ah!

2045
02:29:57,571 --> 02:29:59,072
Whoo!

2046
02:30:00,992 --> 02:30:03,994
Wind us down! Wind us down!

2047
02:30:07,039 --> 02:30:09,416
I don't want the money!

2048
02:30:13,587 --> 02:30:14,796
Look out!

2049
02:30:23,014 --> 02:30:24,264
Get off!

2050
02:30:24,432 --> 02:30:26,433
She's going! Get out of there!

2051
02:31:02,928 --> 02:31:05,972
Emmeline!

2052
02:31:07,058 --> 02:31:09,267
Mama!

2053
02:31:49,934 --> 02:31:52,393
It's all your fault.

2054
02:31:52,561 --> 02:31:55,313
It's your fault from beginning to end.

2055
02:31:55,481 --> 02:31:58,650
You know, even for a policeman...

2056
02:31:58,818 --> 02:32:01,945
...your behavior was ruddy outrageous.

2057
02:32:02,113 --> 02:32:04,739
You could've taken a fair share
like the rest of us...

2058
02:32:04,907 --> 02:32:09,160
...but no, you had to grab up
the whole scene, baby.

2059
02:32:09,328 --> 02:32:14,624
We had $350,000 right in our hands.

2060
02:32:14,792 --> 02:32:18,336
Fourteen into $350,000...

2061
02:32:18,504 --> 02:32:20,880
Shut up.

2062
02:32:23,050 --> 02:32:25,885
I wish I knew what
they were gonna do to us.

2063
02:32:26,053 --> 02:32:31,349
But no matter what happens to us, I hope
what happens to you will be worse.

2064
02:32:33,561 --> 02:32:36,729
I don't think you have to worry
too much about that.

2065
02:32:36,897 --> 02:32:38,857
My wife is divorcing me.

2066
02:32:39,900 --> 02:32:42,652
My mother-in-law
is suing me for damages.

2067
02:32:43,946 --> 02:32:47,574
My daughter is applying to the courts
to have her name changed.

2068
02:32:48,701 --> 02:32:50,743
My pension has been revoked.

2069
02:32:50,911 --> 02:32:54,539
And the only reason
that you 10 idiots...

2070
02:32:55,374 --> 02:32:58,751
...will very likely get off lightly...

2071
02:32:58,919 --> 02:33:03,173
...is because the judge will have
me up there to throw the book at.

2072
02:33:03,340 --> 02:33:05,800
Aw, that's tough. Oh!

2073
02:33:09,597 --> 02:33:14,350
I'd like to think that sometime,
maybe 10 or 20 years from now...

2074
02:33:15,519 --> 02:33:18,730
...there'd be something
I could laugh at, anything.

2075
02:33:28,616 --> 02:33:32,076
Now, see here, you idiots,
it's all your fault because...

2076
02:33:32,244 --> 02:33:34,037
Oh!

2077
02:33:34,205 --> 02:33:38,291
Mama!

2078
02:33:46,133 --> 02:33:48,301
Get away from me!

2079
02:33:48,469 --> 02:33:49,761
Let me go!

